WEBVTT

01:07.940 --> 01:09.691
<i>Troy, you ought
to stop that lying.</i>

01:09.761 --> 01:10.739
<i>I ain't lying.</i>

01:10.820 --> 01:12.539
<i>Nigger had a watermelon this big,</i>

01:12.620 --> 01:14.499
<i>talking about,
"What watermelon, Mr. Rand?"</i>

01:14.580 --> 01:17.259
<i>I'd like to fell out.
"What watermelon, Mr. Rand?"</i>

01:17.460 --> 01:19.139
And it sitting there, big as life.

01:19.220 --> 01:21.337
- What Mr. Rand say?
- He ain't said nothing.

01:21.420 --> 01:22.682
He figure, if the
nigger was too dumb

01:22.752 --> 01:24.015
to know he's carrying
a watermelon,

01:24.100 --> 01:25.898
he wasn't going to get
much sense out of him.

01:25.980 --> 01:28.779
Trying to hide that great, big,
old watermelon under his coat.

01:28.860 --> 01:31.375
Afraid to let the white
man see him carry it home.

01:31.820 --> 01:34.255
I'm like you. I ain't got no
time for them kinda people.

01:34.340 --> 01:35.854
Now, what he look like getting mad

01:35.980 --> 01:37.937
'cause he seen the man from
the union talking to Mr. Rand?

01:38.020 --> 01:41.252
He come up to me, talking about
"Troy Maxson gonna get us fired."

01:41.340 --> 01:43.536
I told him,
"Get away from me with that."

01:43.620 --> 01:46.089
He walked away from me
calling you a troublemaker.

01:46.460 --> 01:48.133
What Mr. Rand say?

01:48.220 --> 01:49.893
He ain't said nothing.
Told me to go down

01:49.980 --> 01:51.778
to the Commissioner's
office next Friday.

01:52.140 --> 01:53.460
They called me down
there to see them.

01:53.580 --> 01:55.844
Well, as long as you got
your complaint filed,

01:55.914 --> 01:56.970
they can't fire you.

01:57.060 --> 01:58.380
That's what one of them
white fellas tell me.

01:58.500 --> 01:59.695
I ain't worried
about them firing me.

01:59.780 --> 02:02.056
What, they gonna fire me
'cause I asked a question?

02:02.140 --> 02:03.210
That's all I did.

02:03.340 --> 02:05.377
I went to Mr. Rand and I asked him.

02:05.460 --> 02:06.450
I asked him, "Why?

02:06.540 --> 02:08.735
"Why you got all the white mens
driving, and the colored lifting?"

02:08.820 --> 02:10.732
Told him, "What's the matter?
Don't I count?

02:10.820 --> 02:12.812
"Think only white fellows got
sense enough to drive a truck?"

02:12.900 --> 02:15.176
"Hell, that ain't no paper job.
Anybody can drive a truck.

02:15.260 --> 02:17.456
"How come you got all the whites
driving and the colored lifting?"

02:20.180 --> 02:22.854
He told me, "Take it to the union."
Well, hell, that's what I done.

02:22.940 --> 02:25.091
Now they want to come up
with this pack of lies.

02:25.180 --> 02:27.615
I told Brownie if the man come
and ask him any questions,

02:27.740 --> 02:29.015
just tell the truth.

02:29.100 --> 02:30.525
Ain't nothing but
somebody trumped it up

02:30.595 --> 02:32.056
on you 'cause you
filed a complaint on.

02:32.140 --> 02:33.415
Brownie ain't got that much sense.

02:33.500 --> 02:34.695
Man wasn't thinking about nothing.

02:34.780 --> 02:36.612
All I want them to do is
change the job description,

02:36.700 --> 02:38.339
give everybody a chance
to drive the truck.

02:40.340 --> 02:43.014
Brownie can't see that.
He ain't got that much sense.

03:04.180 --> 03:05.500
How you figure he be making out

03:05.580 --> 03:08.015
with that gal,
be up in Taylors' all the time?

03:08.100 --> 03:09.819
- That Alberta gal?
- Who?

03:09.900 --> 03:11.220
Brownie.

03:11.300 --> 03:13.690
Same as you and me,
getting about as much as we is.

03:13.780 --> 03:16.249
- Which is to say nothing.
- It is, huh?

03:16.340 --> 03:18.855
Well, I figure you doing
a little better than me.

03:18.940 --> 03:20.499
And I ain't saying what I'm doing!

03:20.820 --> 03:22.459
Nigger, look here. I know you.

03:22.540 --> 03:24.497
If you had gotten
anywhere near that gal,

03:24.580 --> 03:26.811
20 minutes later,
you'd be looking to tell somebody.

03:26.900 --> 03:28.300
And the first one you
gonna want to tell,

03:28.380 --> 03:30.337
that you gonna want to
brag to is going to be me.

03:30.420 --> 03:32.810
I ain't saying that.

03:32.900 --> 03:34.937
I see where you be eyeing her.

03:35.020 --> 03:37.410
I eye all the women.
I don't miss nothing.

03:37.500 --> 03:39.696
Don't never let nobody tell you
Troy Maxson don't eye the women.

03:39.780 --> 03:41.100
Hey,
you been doing more than eyeing her.

03:41.180 --> 03:42.375
You done bought her a drink or two.

03:42.460 --> 03:43.780
Hell, yeah, I bought her a drink.
What that mean?

03:43.860 --> 03:45.055
I bought you one, too.

03:45.140 --> 03:46.779
What that mean,
'cause I buy her a drink?

03:46.900 --> 03:47.711
I'm just being polite.

03:47.781 --> 03:49.256
It's all right to
buy her one drink.

03:49.340 --> 03:51.059
That's what you call being polite.

03:51.140 --> 03:52.859
But when you want to
be buying two or three,

03:52.940 --> 03:54.340
that's what you call eyeing her.

03:54.420 --> 03:56.093
Look here.
As long as you've known me,

03:56.180 --> 03:58.058
you ever known me to
chase after women?

03:58.140 --> 04:01.850
Hell, yeah! Long as I've known you.
You're forgetting, I knew you when.

04:01.940 --> 04:04.694
I'm talking about since
I been married to Rose.

04:04.780 --> 04:06.180
Not since you been married to Rose.

04:06.260 --> 04:07.974
That's the truth, though.
I can say that.

04:08.044 --> 04:09.458
All right then.
Case closed.

04:10.100 --> 04:12.820
I see you be walking up
around Alberta's house.

04:12.900 --> 04:15.699
You supposed to be at Taylors',
and you be walking up around there.

04:15.780 --> 04:16.850
What you watching
where I'm walking for?

04:16.940 --> 04:18.089
I don't be watching after you.

04:18.180 --> 04:20.091
No, I seen you walking
around there more than once.

04:20.180 --> 04:21.534
Hell, you liable to see
me walking anywhere.

04:21.620 --> 04:23.577
That don't mean nothing 'cause
you seen me walking around there.

04:23.660 --> 04:24.855
Where'd she come from, anyway?

04:24.980 --> 04:26.209
She just kinda showed up one day.

04:26.300 --> 04:26.856
Tallahassee.

04:26.926 --> 04:29.611
You can look at that and tell
she one of them Florida gals.

04:29.700 --> 04:31.931
They got some big,
healthy women down there.

04:32.020 --> 04:33.852
Grow them right up
out of the ground.

04:33.940 --> 04:35.499
She got a little bit
of Indian in her.

04:35.580 --> 04:37.458
Most of them niggers in Florida
got some Indian in them.

04:37.540 --> 04:39.577
Yeah,
I don't know about that Indian part,

04:39.660 --> 04:42.619
but she damn sure big and healthy.

04:42.700 --> 04:44.737
Woman wears some big stockings.

04:44.820 --> 04:48.973
Got them crazy big legs, and hips
wide as the Mississippi River.

04:49.060 --> 04:50.540
Legs don't mean nothing.

04:50.620 --> 04:52.213
You don't do nothing but push
'em out of the way.

04:52.340 --> 04:53.899
But them hips,

04:53.980 --> 04:56.939
- they cushion the ride.
- Troy, you ain't got no sense!

04:57.020 --> 05:00.013
It's the truth.
Like you riding on Goodyears!

05:03.180 --> 05:05.137
What you all out here getting into?

05:05.220 --> 05:07.496
What you worried about what
we getting into for, woman?

05:07.580 --> 05:08.616
This is men talk.

05:08.700 --> 05:10.020
What I care what you
all are talking about?

05:10.100 --> 05:11.454
Bono, you gonna stay for supper?

05:11.540 --> 05:12.860
No, thank you, Rose,

05:12.940 --> 05:15.216
but Lucille say she cooking
up a pot of pigfeet.

05:15.300 --> 05:17.337
Pigfeet?
Hell, I'm going home with you.

05:17.420 --> 05:19.776
I might even stay the night,
you got some pigfeet.

05:19.860 --> 05:21.658
You got something in there
to top them pigfeet, Rose?

05:21.740 --> 05:23.971
I'm cooking up some chicken. I got
some chicken and collard greens.

05:24.060 --> 05:25.255
Well, you go on back in the house.

05:25.340 --> 05:26.660
Let me and Bono finish
what we talking about.

05:26.740 --> 05:29.460
This is men talk.
I got some talk for you later.

05:29.540 --> 05:31.532
And you know what kind
of talk I mean, too.

05:31.620 --> 05:33.100
You go on in there and powder it up.

05:33.180 --> 05:34.580
Troy, stop it!

05:35.860 --> 05:37.453
Woman, come here.

05:38.740 --> 05:40.936
Look here, Bono.

05:41.020 --> 05:43.455
When I first met this woman,

05:43.540 --> 05:45.338
I got out that place.

05:45.420 --> 05:48.379
<i>Hitch up my pony, saddle up my mare</i>

05:48.460 --> 05:51.100
<i>There's a woman out
there for me somewhere</i>

05:51.180 --> 05:55.094
I looked at here, looked at there,
saw Rose, and I latched on to her.

05:55.180 --> 05:56.864
I latched on to her
and I told her...

05:56.934 --> 05:58.571
Now,
I'm gonna tell you the truth.

05:58.860 --> 06:03.139
I latched on to her and told her,
"Baby, I don't want to marry.

06:03.220 --> 06:04.859
"I just want to be your man."

06:04.940 --> 06:07.375
Rose told me...
Tell him what you told me, Ro.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.298
I told him if he wasn't
the marrying kind,

06:09.380 --> 06:11.611
then move out of the way,
so the marrying kind could find me.

06:11.700 --> 06:14.135
That's what she told me,
"Nigger, you in my way.

06:14.220 --> 06:15.540
"You blocking the view.

06:15.620 --> 06:17.577
"Move out the way,
so I can find me a husband."

06:17.660 --> 06:20.095
- I thought it over 2-3 days.
- Two-three days, nothing.

06:20.220 --> 06:21.654
You was back the same night.

06:21.740 --> 06:23.891
I come back, told her, "Okay, baby,

06:23.980 --> 06:25.778
"but I'm gonna buy
me a banty rooster

06:25.860 --> 06:27.499
"and put him out
there in the backyard.

06:27.580 --> 06:29.014
"And when he see a stranger come,

06:29.100 --> 06:30.500
"he gonna flap his wings and crow."

06:30.580 --> 06:32.651
Look here, Bono. I done watched
that front door by myself.

06:32.740 --> 06:35.494
It was that back door
I was worried about.

06:35.580 --> 06:38.015
Don't talk like that!
Troy, you're not but telling a lie.

06:38.340 --> 06:41.229
Only thing was, we first got
married, nforget the rooster.

06:41.299 --> 06:42.414
We ain't had no yard.

06:42.500 --> 06:43.650
I hear you tell it.

06:43.740 --> 06:46.130
Me and Lucille was staying
down there on Logan Street.

06:46.220 --> 06:48.689
Had two rooms with the
outhouse in the back.

06:48.780 --> 06:50.373
I ain't mind the outhouse none.

06:50.500 --> 06:52.969
But when that goddamn wind blew
through there in the winter,

06:53.060 --> 06:54.779
that's what I'm talking about!

06:55.100 --> 06:55.694
To this day,

06:55.764 --> 06:58.980
I wonder why the hell I ever stayed
down there for six long years.

06:59.060 --> 07:01.529
But, see,
I didn't know I could do no better.

07:01.620 --> 07:04.340
I thought only white folks
had inside toilets and things.

07:04.420 --> 07:05.615
A lot of folks don't think

07:05.700 --> 07:07.259
they can do no better
than they're doing now.

07:07.340 --> 07:08.730
Just something you gotta learn.

07:08.800 --> 07:10.458
A lot of folks still
shop at Bella's.

07:10.540 --> 07:12.133
Ain't nothing wrong with Bella's.
She got fresh food.

07:12.220 --> 07:14.052
I ain't said nothing about
if she got fresh food.

07:14.140 --> 07:15.460
I'm talking about what she charge.

07:15.540 --> 07:17.418
She charges 10 cents
more than the A&P.

07:17.500 --> 07:19.059
A&P ain't never done nothing for me.

07:19.140 --> 07:20.972
I spend my money where
I'm treated right.

07:21.060 --> 07:22.380
I go down to Bella, say,

07:22.460 --> 07:24.895
"I need a loaf of bread, I'll pay
you Friday," she gives it to me.

07:24.980 --> 07:26.812
What sense that make
when I got money

07:26.900 --> 07:28.220
to spend it somewhere else

07:28.300 --> 07:29.893
and ignore the person
who done right by me?

07:29.980 --> 07:31.016
That ain't in the Bible.

07:31.100 --> 07:32.375
We ain't talking about
what's in the Bible.

07:32.500 --> 07:34.651
What sense it make to shop
there when she overcharges?

07:34.740 --> 07:36.220
Well, you do your shopping
where you want to,

07:36.340 --> 07:37.854
I do my shopping where
people been good to me.

07:37.940 --> 07:39.897
I don't think it's right for
her to overcharge, that's all.

07:39.980 --> 07:41.130
Look here, I got to be getting on.

07:41.260 --> 07:42.660
Lucille gonna be raising
all kind of hell.

07:42.780 --> 07:44.339
Where you going, nigger?
We ain't finished this pint.

07:44.420 --> 07:45.536
Come here finish this pint.

07:45.700 --> 07:49.580
Well, hell, I am,
if you ever turn the bottle loose.

07:49.660 --> 07:51.718
Only thing I'll say
about the A&P is,

07:51.788 --> 07:54.018
I'm glad Cory got
that job down there.

07:54.300 --> 07:55.893
Help him with his school
clothes and things.

07:55.980 --> 07:58.290
Gabe done moved out,
things getting tight around here.

07:58.380 --> 07:59.609
He got that job,

07:59.700 --> 08:01.259
he can start to look
out for himself.

08:01.340 --> 08:04.572
Cory done got recruited by
a college football team.

08:04.700 --> 08:07.818
I told that boy about that
college football stuff.

08:07.900 --> 08:10.699
The white man ain't gonna let him
get nowhere with that football.

08:10.780 --> 08:12.772
I told him when he first
come to me with it.

08:12.860 --> 08:15.455
Now, you come telling me he
done got more tied up in it.

08:15.540 --> 08:17.611
He ought to get recruited
in how to fix cars,

08:17.700 --> 08:18.895
or some way he can make a living.

08:19.020 --> 08:21.410
He ain't talking about making
no living playing football.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.492
It's just something
the boys in school do.

08:23.580 --> 08:25.697
They're gonna send a recruiter by
to talk to you. He'll tell you.

08:25.780 --> 08:27.772
He ain't talking about making
no living playing football.

08:27.860 --> 08:29.374
It's an honor to be recruited.

08:29.460 --> 08:31.895
It ain't gonna get him nowhere,
Bono'll tell you that.

08:32.220 --> 08:35.258
If he be like you in sports,
he gonna be all right.

08:35.340 --> 08:37.808
Ain't but two men ever
played baseball good as you.

08:37.940 --> 08:39.977
That's Babe Ruth and Josh Gibson.

08:40.059 --> 08:42.211
Them the only two men ever
hit more home runs than you.

08:42.299 --> 08:44.576
And what it ever get me?
I ain't got a pot to piss in,

08:44.700 --> 08:45.975
or a window to throw it out of.

08:46.060 --> 08:47.813
Times have changed since you
were playing baseball, Troy.

08:47.900 --> 08:49.937
That was before the war.
Times have changed a lot since then.

08:50.020 --> 08:51.090
How the hell they done changed?

08:51.180 --> 08:52.694
They got a lot of colored
boys playing ball now.

08:52.780 --> 08:54.134
Baseball and football.

08:54.220 --> 08:57.258
You right about that, Ro.
Times have changed, Troy.

08:57.340 --> 08:58.694
You just come along too early.

08:58.780 --> 09:02.456
There ought not never have been
no time called "too early."

09:03.980 --> 09:06.211
Now you take that fellow...

09:06.300 --> 09:07.548
What's that fellow
they had playing

09:07.618 --> 09:08.974
right field back then
for the Yankees?

09:09.060 --> 09:10.130
You remember who I'm talking about,
Bono,

09:10.220 --> 09:11.176
played right field for The Yankees.

09:11.260 --> 09:12.899
- Selkirk?
- Yeah, Selkirk, that's it!

09:13.020 --> 09:16.331
Man's batting 269, you understand?
269!

09:16.420 --> 09:20.130
What sense that make?
I'm batting 432 with 37 home runs!

09:20.220 --> 09:23.213
He's batting 269,
playing right field for the Yankees!

09:23.300 --> 09:25.417
I saw Josh Gibson's
daughter yesterday.

09:25.500 --> 09:28.174
She's running around with
raggedy shoes on her feet.

09:28.260 --> 09:29.819
I bet you Selkirk's daughter
ain't running around

09:29.900 --> 09:31.698
with no raggedy shoes on her feet.
I bet you that.

09:31.780 --> 09:33.612
They got a lot of colored
baseball players now.

09:33.700 --> 09:34.850
Jackie Robinson was the first.

09:34.940 --> 09:36.374
Folks had to wait
for Jackie Robinson.

09:36.500 --> 09:38.232
I done seen 100
niggers play baseball

09:38.302 --> 09:39.698
better than Jackie Robinson.

09:39.780 --> 09:42.693
Hell, I seen some teams Jackie
Robinson couldn't even make!

09:42.780 --> 09:44.055
What you talking about,
Jackie Robinson?

09:44.140 --> 09:45.813
Jackie Robinson wasn't nobody!

09:45.900 --> 09:47.300
I'm talking about if
you could play ball,

09:47.380 --> 09:48.700
then they ought to let you play.

09:48.780 --> 09:49.975
Don't matter what color you are.

09:50.060 --> 09:51.699
Telling me I come along too early.

09:51.780 --> 09:55.057
If you can play,
then they ought to let you play.

09:55.140 --> 09:56.870
You gonna drink yourself to death.

09:56.940 --> 09:58.975
You don't need to be
drinking like that.

09:59.980 --> 10:01.539
Death ain't nothing.
I done seen him,

10:01.620 --> 10:03.930
I done wrestled with him. You
can't tell me nothing about death.

10:04.020 --> 10:07.297
Death ain't nothing but a
fastball on the outside corner,

10:07.380 --> 10:11.215
and you know what I do with that.
Look here, Bono, am I lying?

10:11.300 --> 10:14.134
You get one of them
fastballs about waist high

10:14.220 --> 10:15.813
on the outside corner of the plate

10:15.900 --> 10:17.619
where you can get the
meat of the bat on it,

10:17.700 --> 10:20.932
and, good God,
you could kiss it good-bye.

10:21.020 --> 10:22.977
- Am I lying?
- No, you telling the truth.

10:23.140 --> 10:24.574
I seen you do it.

10:24.660 --> 10:29.780
If I'm lying, that's 450 feet worth
of lying. That's all death is to me.

10:29.860 --> 10:32.295
A fastball on the outside corner.

10:32.380 --> 10:34.690
I don't know why you want to
get on talking about death?

10:34.780 --> 10:36.100
Ain't nothing wrong with
talking about death.

10:36.180 --> 10:37.899
That's a part of life!
Everybody gonna die.

10:38.020 --> 10:39.295
You gonna die. I'm gonna die.

10:39.380 --> 10:41.178
Bono gonna die.
Hell, we all gonna die.

10:41.260 --> 10:43.616
But you ain't got to talk about it.
I don't like talking about it.

10:43.700 --> 10:44.895
Well, you the one brought it up.

10:44.980 --> 10:46.539
Me and Bono talking about baseball.

10:46.620 --> 10:48.577
You come telling me I'm
gonna drink myself to death.

10:48.660 --> 10:49.935
Ain't that right, Bono?

10:50.020 --> 10:52.251
Now you know I drink just
but one night out the week,

10:52.340 --> 10:53.490
that's Friday night.

10:53.620 --> 10:55.293
I drink just enough to
where I can handle it.

10:55.380 --> 10:56.894
Then I leaves it alone.
I cuts it loose.

10:56.980 --> 10:59.017
So, you ain't got to worry about
me drinking myself to death

10:59.140 --> 11:00.699
'cause I ain't worrying about death.

11:00.780 --> 11:03.454
I done seen him,
done wrestled with him.

11:03.540 --> 11:04.815
Look here, Bono.

11:04.900 --> 11:05.909
I look up one day,

11:05.979 --> 11:08.052
and Death is marching
straight at me,

11:08.140 --> 11:10.257
like soldiers on parade.

11:10.340 --> 11:12.696
The Army of Death was
marching straight at me.

11:12.780 --> 11:16.137
It was the middle of July, 1941.

11:16.220 --> 11:18.451
And it got real cold,
just like it be winter.

11:18.540 --> 11:20.133
And it seemed like Death, himself,

11:20.220 --> 11:22.257
reached out and touched
me on the shoulder.

11:22.340 --> 11:25.617
He touched me like I touch you now.
I got cold as ice.

11:25.700 --> 11:26.975
Death standing there,
grinning at me.

11:27.060 --> 11:28.779
Troy, why don't you hush that talk.

11:28.860 --> 11:32.137
I said, "What you want, Mr. Death?
You be wanting me?

11:32.220 --> 11:34.098
"You done sent your
army to be getting me?"

11:34.180 --> 11:35.136
I looked him dead in the eye.

11:35.220 --> 11:36.290
I wasn't fearing nothing.

11:36.380 --> 11:39.054
I was ready to tangle,
just like I'm ready to tangle now!

11:39.420 --> 11:41.298
Bible says be ever vigilant.

11:41.380 --> 11:43.690
So, I don't get but so drunk.
I got to keep watch.

11:43.780 --> 11:45.373
Troy was right down
there at Mercy Hospital.

11:45.460 --> 11:46.814
You remember he had that pneumonia,

11:46.900 --> 11:48.812
laying there with a fever,
talking plumb out his head.

11:48.900 --> 11:50.175
And Death standing there,
staring at me,

11:50.300 --> 11:51.700
carrying that sickle in his hand.

11:51.780 --> 11:57.538
Finally, he say, "You want to
be bound over for another year?"

11:57.620 --> 11:59.771
Just like that. He say,

11:59.860 --> 12:03.649
"You want to be bound
over for another year?"

12:03.740 --> 12:07.734
I said, "Bound over, hell!
We can settle this right now."

12:07.860 --> 12:11.251
He kinda fell back when I said that.
And all the cold went out of me.

12:11.340 --> 12:13.332
I reached down,
I grabbed that sickle.

12:13.540 --> 12:15.213
I threw it as far
as I could throw it,

12:15.300 --> 12:16.973
and me and him
commenced to wrestling.

12:17.060 --> 12:20.576
We wrestled for... Carry the six...
Three days and three nights!

12:20.660 --> 12:22.970
Now, I don't know where
I got the strength from,

12:23.060 --> 12:24.779
'cause every time he tried
to get the best of me,

12:24.860 --> 12:26.781
I reached way deep
down inside myself,

12:26.851 --> 12:28.979
found the strength to
do him one better.

12:29.060 --> 12:30.653
Every time Troy tells that story,

12:30.740 --> 12:31.969
he find different ways to tell it,

12:32.060 --> 12:33.540
different things to make up.

12:33.620 --> 12:35.020
I ain't making up nothing, woman.

12:35.100 --> 12:36.659
I'm telling you the
facts of what happened.

12:36.740 --> 12:39.016
I wrestled with Death for
three days and three nights,

12:39.140 --> 12:41.575
and I'm standing here
to tell you about it.

12:43.900 --> 12:45.937
All right.
At the end of the third night,

12:46.020 --> 12:49.092
we done weakened each other to
where we can't even hardly move.

12:49.180 --> 12:50.170
Death stood up.

12:50.260 --> 12:52.456
He threw on that robe,
had a white robe with a hood on it.

12:52.580 --> 12:55.857
He throwed on that robe and went
off to look for that sickle.

12:55.940 --> 12:59.616
He said, "I'll be back."
Just like that. "I'll be back."

12:59.700 --> 13:02.818
I said, "Yeah?
Well, you gonna have to find me!"

13:02.900 --> 13:04.016
I wasn't no fool.

13:04.500 --> 13:05.900
I wasn't going looking for him.

13:05.980 --> 13:08.540
I know Death ain't nothing to play
with. And I know he's gonna get me.

13:08.620 --> 13:11.658
I know I got to join his army,
his camp followers.

13:11.740 --> 13:14.619
But as long as I keep up my
strength and see him coming,

13:14.700 --> 13:18.580
as long as I keep up my vigilance,
he gonna have to fight to get me.

13:18.660 --> 13:19.935
I ain't going easy.

13:20.340 --> 13:24.016
Well, look here, since you
got to keep up your vigilance,

13:24.100 --> 13:25.534
let me have the bottle.

13:25.620 --> 13:27.532
Hell,
I shouldn't have told you that part.

13:27.620 --> 13:28.736
I should have left out that part.

13:28.820 --> 13:30.300
Troy be talking all that stuff.

13:30.380 --> 13:32.736
Half the time, he don't even
know what he be talking about!

13:32.860 --> 13:33.876
Yeah,
Bono know me better than that.

13:33.946 --> 13:34.817
That's right, I know you.

13:34.900 --> 13:38.098
I know you got some Uncle
Remus in your blood.

13:38.180 --> 13:40.456
You got more stories than
the devil got sinners.

13:40.540 --> 13:43.135
Hell, I done seen him, too.
Done talked to the devil.

13:43.220 --> 13:44.859
Nobody wants to be
hearing that stuff!

13:47.740 --> 13:48.935
Hey, Pop.

13:49.020 --> 13:50.534
What you come "Hey, Poppin'" me for?

13:50.620 --> 13:52.691
How you doing, Rose?

13:52.780 --> 13:55.295
Mr. Bono, how you doing?

13:55.380 --> 13:57.053
Hey, Lyons, how you been?

13:57.140 --> 13:58.574
He must've been doing all right.

13:58.660 --> 13:59.810
I ain't seen him
around here last week.

13:59.900 --> 14:01.539
Troy, leave your boy alone.
He come by to see you

14:01.620 --> 14:03.134
and you want to start
all that nonsense.

14:03.220 --> 14:04.540
I ain't bothering Lyons.
Here, get you a drink.

14:04.620 --> 14:06.100
Me and him got an understanding.

14:06.180 --> 14:09.332
I know why he come by to see me,
and he know I know.

14:09.420 --> 14:11.298
Come on, Pop.
I just stopped by to say hi,

14:11.380 --> 14:12.450
see how you was doing.

14:12.540 --> 14:14.532
- You ain't stopped by yesterday.
- You staying for supper, Lyons?

14:14.620 --> 14:15.849
I got some chicken
cooking in the oven.

14:15.940 --> 14:17.738
No, Rose, thanks.
I just was in the neighborhood

14:17.820 --> 14:19.220
and thought I'd stop
by for a minute.

14:19.300 --> 14:20.780
Yeah, you was in the
neighborhood all right.

14:20.860 --> 14:22.135
Nigger, you telling the truth there.

14:22.220 --> 14:23.973
You was in the neighborhood
'cause it's my payday.

14:24.060 --> 14:26.291
Well, hell, since you mentioned it,
let me have $10.

14:27.020 --> 14:30.138
I'll be damned.
I'll die and go to hell

14:30.220 --> 14:32.689
and play blackjack with the
devil before I give you $10.

14:32.780 --> 14:35.659
That's what I want to know about,
that devil you done seen.

14:35.740 --> 14:37.891
Pop done seen the devil?
You too much, Pop.

14:37.980 --> 14:40.211
- Yeah, I done seen him.
- He ain't seen no devil.

14:40.300 --> 14:42.417
I told him that man ain't had
nothing to do with the devil.

14:42.500 --> 14:44.571
Anything he can't understand,
he want to call it the devil.

14:44.660 --> 14:47.858
Look here, Bono. I go by
Hertzberger's to get some furniture.

14:47.940 --> 14:50.739
You got three rooms for $298.
That what it say on the radio.

14:50.820 --> 14:54.177
"Three rooms, $298."
He made up a little song about it.

14:54.260 --> 14:57.253
I get down there,
man tell me I can't get no credit.

14:57.340 --> 14:59.571
I'm working every day,
can't get no credit.

14:59.660 --> 15:00.776
What to do?

15:00.900 --> 15:02.573
I got an empty house with
some raggedy furniture.

15:02.700 --> 15:03.816
Cory ain't got no bed.

15:03.900 --> 15:06.017
He's sleeping on a pile
of rags on the floor.

15:06.100 --> 15:08.137
Working every day,
can't get no credit.

15:08.220 --> 15:09.620
I come back here, Rose'll tell you,

15:09.700 --> 15:11.578
madder than hell,
trying to figure out what to do.

15:11.900 --> 15:13.016
Come a knock on the door.

15:13.100 --> 15:15.137
I ain't been living but three days,
who know I'm here?

15:15.260 --> 15:17.377
I open the door.
Devil standing there.

15:17.460 --> 15:18.496
Bigger than life.

15:18.580 --> 15:20.458
White fella,
got on good clothes and everything.

15:20.540 --> 15:21.690
Standing there with a
clipboard in his hand.

15:21.780 --> 15:23.055
Now, I ain't got to say nothing.

15:23.180 --> 15:24.614
First words come out of his mouth,

15:24.700 --> 15:27.534
"I understand you need some
furniture and can't get no credit."

15:27.620 --> 15:31.091
I liked to fell over. He said, "I'll
give you all the credit you want,

15:31.180 --> 15:33.172
"but you gonna have to
pay the interest on it."

15:33.260 --> 15:34.694
Now, I told him,
he give me them three rooms,

15:34.780 --> 15:36.260
he can charge whatever he want.

15:36.340 --> 15:37.979
Next day, a truck pull up here,

15:38.060 --> 15:39.699
two men unload them three rooms.

15:39.820 --> 15:42.016
Man what drove the
truck give me a book.

15:42.100 --> 15:45.537
Said first of the month,
send $10 to the address in the book,

15:45.660 --> 15:46.730
everything'll be fine.

15:46.820 --> 15:48.300
Said if you miss a payment,

15:48.380 --> 15:51.054
the devil was coming back,
and there'll be hell to pay.

15:51.140 --> 15:52.654
That was 15 years ago.

15:52.740 --> 15:56.256
To this day, first day of
every month, I send my $10,

15:56.380 --> 15:57.734
just like clockwork.
Rose'll tell you.

15:57.820 --> 16:00.654
- Troy lying.
- I ain't never seen that man since.

16:00.740 --> 16:01.309
Now, you tell me,

16:01.379 --> 16:02.618
who else that gonna
be but the devil?

16:02.700 --> 16:04.771
And I ain't sold my soul
or nothing like that.

16:04.860 --> 16:07.580
No, I wouldn't have truck with
the devil over nothing like that.

16:07.660 --> 16:11.256
But I got my furniture. And I
send my $10, just like clockwork.

16:11.340 --> 16:14.219
How long you say you been
paying this $10 a month?

16:14.300 --> 16:15.336
15 years.

16:15.420 --> 16:17.413
Hell, ain't you finished
paying for it yet?

16:17.483 --> 16:19.096
How much the man
done charge you?

16:19.180 --> 16:22.412
Hell, I done paid for it.
I done paid for it 10 times over.

16:22.500 --> 16:23.775
Fact is, I'm scared to stop paying.

16:23.860 --> 16:26.295
Troy lying. We got that
furniture from Mr. Glickman.

16:26.380 --> 16:28.099
He ain't paying no
$10 a month to nobody.

16:28.180 --> 16:30.456
Hell, woman,
Bono know I ain't that big a fool.

16:30.580 --> 16:31.698
I was just getting ready to say,

16:31.768 --> 16:33.095
I know where there's
a bridge for sale.

16:33.180 --> 16:34.250
I'll tell you this.

16:34.340 --> 16:36.093
It don't matter to me
if it was the devil.

16:36.180 --> 16:37.534
It don't matter if
the devil give credit.

16:37.620 --> 16:39.532
- Somebody got to give it.
- It ought to matter.

16:39.620 --> 16:41.896
You walking around here saying you
gonna make truck with the devil,

16:41.980 --> 16:43.414
God's the one you're
gonna have to answer to.

16:43.500 --> 16:45.014
He's the one gonna
be at the Judgment.

16:45.100 --> 16:47.012
Yeah, well, look here,
Pop, let me have that $10.

16:47.140 --> 16:48.256
I'll give it back to you.

16:48.340 --> 16:49.774
Bonnie got a job
working at the hospital.

16:49.860 --> 16:50.930
Bono, what did I tell you?

16:51.060 --> 16:52.619
Only time I see this nigger
is when he want something.

16:52.700 --> 16:53.850
That's the only time I see him.

16:54.100 --> 16:56.490
Come on, Pop, Mr. Bono
don't want to hear all that.

16:56.580 --> 16:58.776
Let me have the $10.
I told you, Bonnie's working!

16:58.940 --> 17:00.215
What that mean to me
if Bonnie's working?

17:00.300 --> 17:03.452
I don't care if she working.
Go ask her for $10 if she's working.

17:03.540 --> 17:06.214
Talking about Bonnie working.
Why ain't you working?

17:06.619 --> 17:08.656
Pop,
you know I can't find no decent job.

17:08.740 --> 17:10.696
Where am I gonna get a job at?
You know I can't get no job.

17:10.900 --> 17:13.096
I told you,
I know some people down there.

17:13.180 --> 17:15.012
I can get you on the
rubbish if you want to work.

17:15.099 --> 17:17.898
I told you that last time you come
back here asking for something.

17:17.980 --> 17:19.255
No, Pop, thanks, that ain't for me.

17:19.380 --> 17:20.859
I don't want to be
carrying nobody's rubbish.

17:20.940 --> 17:22.771
I don't want to be punching
nobody's time clock.

17:22.859 --> 17:24.852
What's the matter? You too
good to carry people's rubbish?

17:24.940 --> 17:26.818
Where you think that $10 you
talking about comes from?

17:26.900 --> 17:28.653
I'm just supposed to
haul people's rubbish

17:28.740 --> 17:30.618
and give my money to you
'cause you too lazy to work?

17:30.700 --> 17:31.816
You're too lazy to work

17:31.900 --> 17:33.493
and want to know why you
ain't got what I got.

17:33.580 --> 17:35.219
What hospital Bonnie working at,
Mercy?

17:35.300 --> 17:37.053
She down at Passavant,
working in the laundry.

17:37.140 --> 17:38.972
I ain't got nothing as it is.
I give you $10,

17:39.060 --> 17:40.414
I got to eat beans
the rest of the week?

17:40.500 --> 17:41.900
No,
you ain't getting no $10 over here.

17:42.020 --> 17:43.500
You ain't got to be eating no beans.

17:43.580 --> 17:44.855
I don't know why you
want to say that?

17:44.940 --> 17:46.772
I ain't got no extra money!

17:48.660 --> 17:49.810
Gabe done moved out,

17:49.900 --> 17:52.256
giving his money over there to
Miss Pearl, paying her rent.

17:52.340 --> 17:53.535
Things done got tight around here.

17:53.620 --> 17:55.100
I can't afford to be
giving you every payday.

17:55.180 --> 17:56.626
I ain't asked you
to give me nothing.

17:56.696 --> 17:57.820
I asked you to loan me $10.

17:57.900 --> 17:58.970
I know you got $10.

17:59.060 --> 18:01.177
Yeah, I got it.
You know why I got it?

18:01.260 --> 18:03.536
'Cause I don't throw my
money away on them streets.

18:03.620 --> 18:05.657
You want to live the fast life,
being a musician,

18:05.740 --> 18:07.379
running around in
them clubs and things,

18:07.460 --> 18:08.894
then learn to take care of yourself.

18:08.980 --> 18:12.132
You ain't gone find me
asking nobody for nothing!

18:12.220 --> 18:13.540
I spent too many years without.

18:13.620 --> 18:15.054
Hey,
you and me is two different people.

18:15.140 --> 18:18.372
I done learned my mistake and I
learned to do what's right by it.

18:18.460 --> 18:20.133
You still trying to get
something for nothing.

18:20.220 --> 18:21.370
Life don't owe you nothing.

18:21.460 --> 18:24.055
You owe it to yourself. Ask Bono.
He'll tell you I'm right.

18:24.140 --> 18:26.575
You got your way of dealing
with the world, I got mine.

18:26.660 --> 18:28.458
Only thing that matters
to me is the music.

18:28.820 --> 18:30.891
Yeah, I can see that.
Don't matter how you gonna eat,

18:30.980 --> 18:32.334
don't matter where your
next dollar coming from.

18:32.420 --> 18:33.900
Yeah, you telling the truth there.

18:33.980 --> 18:36.051
I know I got to eat.
But I got to live, too.

18:36.300 --> 18:38.531
I need something that's gonna help
me get out of bed in the morning,

18:38.620 --> 18:40.134
make me feel like I
belong in the world.

18:40.220 --> 18:41.893
I don't bother nobody.

18:41.980 --> 18:43.130
I just stay with my music

18:43.220 --> 18:45.371
'cause that's the only way I
can find to live in the world.

18:45.460 --> 18:48.055
Otherwise,
ain't no telling what I might do.

18:48.140 --> 18:51.019
I don't come by criticizing
you and how you live.

18:51.340 --> 18:53.059
I just come by to ask you for $10.

18:53.180 --> 18:55.251
I don't want to hear all
that about how I live.

18:55.340 --> 18:57.775
Boy, your mama did a hell
of a job raising you.

18:57.860 --> 19:00.534
You can't change me, Pop.
I'm 34 years old.

19:01.340 --> 19:02.535
If you wanted to change me,

19:02.620 --> 19:04.373
you should have been there
when I was growing up.

19:04.860 --> 19:07.250
I come by to see you,
ask you for $10,

19:07.340 --> 19:10.094
and you want to talk
about how I was raised?

19:10.180 --> 19:13.696
You don't know nothing
about how I was raised.

19:19.220 --> 19:21.610
Let the boy have $10, Troy.

19:25.980 --> 19:28.893
Hell you looking at?
You know I ain't got no money.

19:28.980 --> 19:30.812
You know what I do with my money.

19:30.900 --> 19:32.732
Go on, give him $10 if
you want him to have it.

19:33.100 --> 19:36.138
I will, soon as you turn it loose.

19:39.060 --> 19:40.972
There it is.

19:41.060 --> 19:43.097
Seventy six dollars
and twenty-two cents.

19:43.620 --> 19:46.454
You see this, Bono? I ain't
gonna get but six of that back.

19:46.540 --> 19:49.533
He ought to stop telling that lie.
Here, Lyons.

19:49.820 --> 19:50.970
Thanks, Rose.

19:56.300 --> 19:57.654
Look, I got to run.
I'll see you all later.

19:57.740 --> 19:59.891
Wait a minute.
You gonna say, "Thanks, Rose,"

19:59.980 --> 20:01.812
but you ain't gonna look to see
where she got that money from.

20:01.900 --> 20:04.017
- You see how they do me, Bono?
- I know she got it from you, Pop.

20:04.100 --> 20:06.456
- Thanks. I'll give it back to you.
- There you go, telling another lie.

20:06.540 --> 20:08.771
Time I see that $10,
you'll be owing me $30 more.

20:08.860 --> 20:10.738
- See you, Mr. Bono.
- Take care, Lyons.

20:11.500 --> 20:13.890
Thanks, Pop. I'll see you again.

20:15.340 --> 20:18.333
I don't know why that boy don't
go and get him a decent job

20:18.420 --> 20:19.695
and take care of that woman he got.

20:19.780 --> 20:22.295
He'll be all right, Troy.
The boy is still young!

20:22.540 --> 20:26.011
- The boy is 34 years old.
- Let's not get off into all that.

20:26.100 --> 20:29.252
Look here, I got to go. I got to
be going. Lucille gonna be waiting.

20:29.340 --> 20:33.414
See this woman, Bono?
I love this woman.

20:34.020 --> 20:36.933
I love her so much, it hurts.

20:37.020 --> 20:41.060
I love her so much, I done
run out of ways of loving her,

20:41.140 --> 20:43.371
so, I got to get back to basics.

20:43.620 --> 20:45.213
Don't you come by my
house Monday morning,

20:45.300 --> 20:46.450
talking about time to go to work.

20:46.540 --> 20:47.955
'Cause I'm gonna
still be stroking.

20:48.025 --> 20:48.691
Troy, stop!

20:48.780 --> 20:52.091
I ain't paying him no mind, Rose.
That ain't nothing but gin talk.

20:52.180 --> 20:54.217
Go on, Troy! I'll see you Monday.

20:54.300 --> 20:56.531
Don't you come by my house, nigger!

20:58.300 --> 21:00.451
I done told you what
I'm gonna be doing!

21:02.860 --> 21:04.977
Come back on Tuesday!

21:31.060 --> 21:34.337
<i>Jesus be a fence</i>

21:34.900 --> 21:37.176
<i>All around me</i>

21:37.260 --> 21:39.058
<i>Every day</i>

21:44.660 --> 21:46.538
Good morning.

21:46.620 --> 21:48.577
You ready for breakfast?
I can fix you some

21:48.660 --> 21:50.936
soon as I finish hanging
up these clothes.

21:51.020 --> 21:53.202
I got the coffee on.
That's all right.

21:53.272 --> 21:55.572
I just have some of
that this morning.

21:57.620 --> 22:00.089
That 651 hit yesterday.

22:00.180 --> 22:03.014
That's the second time this month
Miss Pearl hit for a dollar.

22:03.100 --> 22:05.410
Seems like those that need
the least always get lucky.

22:05.540 --> 22:06.690
Poor folks can't get nothing.

22:06.780 --> 22:08.100
Them numbers don't know nobody.

22:08.180 --> 22:10.331
I don't know why you fool with 'em,
you and Lyons both.

22:10.460 --> 22:11.940
It's something to do.

22:12.020 --> 22:14.296
You ain't doing nothing but
throwing your money away.

22:14.380 --> 22:15.939
Troy,
you know I don't play foolishly.

22:16.020 --> 22:17.613
I just play a nickel
here and a nickel there.

22:17.700 --> 22:19.214
That's two nickels
you done throwed away.

22:19.300 --> 22:21.940
Nah, I hit sometimes.
That makes up for it.

22:22.020 --> 22:23.534
Always comes in handy when I do hit.

22:23.620 --> 22:24.770
I don't hear you complaining then.

22:24.860 --> 22:26.738
I ain't complaining now.
I just say it's foolish,

22:26.820 --> 22:29.972
trying to guess out of 600 ways
which way the number gonna come.

22:30.060 --> 22:31.619
If I had all the
money these niggers...

22:35.300 --> 22:39.214
You negroes throw away
on numbers in one week,

22:39.300 --> 22:42.134
just one week, I'd be a rich man.

22:42.220 --> 22:43.700
You wishing and calling it foolish

22:43.780 --> 22:45.373
ain't gonna stop folks
from playing the numbers.

22:45.460 --> 22:47.497
That's one thing for sure.

22:47.580 --> 22:50.732
Besides, some good things
come from playing numbers.

22:50.820 --> 22:53.779
Look where Pope done bought him
that restaurant off of numbers.

22:53.860 --> 22:58.491
I can't stand niggers like that. Man
ain't had two dimes to rub together.

22:58.580 --> 23:01.300
He running around with
his shoes all run-over,

23:01.380 --> 23:03.372
bumming money for cigarettes.

23:03.460 --> 23:06.373
All right.
Got lucky there, hit the numbers...

23:06.460 --> 23:07.814
Troy, I know all about it.

23:07.900 --> 23:10.654
Had good sense. I'll say that for
him. Man ain't throw his money away.

23:10.740 --> 23:14.575
I done see niggers go
through $2,000 in four days.

23:14.660 --> 23:17.175
Man built him that
restaurant down there.

23:17.260 --> 23:18.774
Fix it up real nice, too.

23:18.860 --> 23:20.738
Then he won't let nobody come in it.

23:20.820 --> 23:23.130
Negro go in there,
can't get no kind of service.

23:23.220 --> 23:26.497
Seen a white fella go in there,
he orders a bowl of stew.

23:26.620 --> 23:28.851
Pope pick all the meat
out of the pot for him.

23:28.940 --> 23:30.897
Man ain't had nothing
but a bowl of meat!

23:30.980 --> 23:32.460
Negro go in there behind him,

23:32.540 --> 23:34.497
he ain't got nothing but the
potatoes and the carrots.

23:34.580 --> 23:36.697
Talking about what
numbers do for people.

23:36.780 --> 23:38.009
You picked the wrong example there.

23:38.100 --> 23:40.171
Ain't done nothing but made
a worser fool out of him

23:40.300 --> 23:42.053
than he already was before.

23:43.740 --> 23:45.220
Troy.

23:45.300 --> 23:48.532
You ought to stop worrying about
what happened at work yesterday.

23:50.820 --> 23:52.140
I ain't worried.

23:53.700 --> 23:55.771
Just called me down there,
the Commissioner's office,

23:55.900 --> 23:58.540
everybody's worried
about them firing me.

23:58.620 --> 24:01.499
I ain't worrying
about them firing me.

24:01.580 --> 24:03.811
You ain't got to worry about that.

24:03.900 --> 24:06.051
