30:10.540 --> 30:12.497
Where's Gabe?

30:12.580 --> 30:14.492
He's gone off somewhere.

30:17.140 --> 30:18.256
He ain't eating right.

30:18.340 --> 30:20.297
Miss Pearl say she can't
get him to eat nothing.

30:20.380 --> 30:21.655
What you want me to do about it,
Rose?

30:21.740 --> 30:23.664
I did everything I
could for the man.

30:23.734 --> 30:25.177
I can't make him get well.

30:25.260 --> 30:28.458
Man got half his head blown off,
what you expect?

30:28.540 --> 30:30.213
Seems like something ought
to be done to help him.

30:30.300 --> 30:31.620
The man don't bother nobody.

30:31.700 --> 30:34.056
He just mixed up
'cause of that metal plate

30:34.140 --> 30:36.814
he got in his head.
Ain't no sense in...

30:36.900 --> 30:39.938
Thank you. Ain't no sense in
sending him to the hospital.

30:40.020 --> 30:41.340
At least he'd be eating right.

30:41.420 --> 30:42.820
They could help him
take care of himself.

30:42.900 --> 30:44.493
Don't nobody want to be locked up,
Rose.

30:44.580 --> 30:46.458
What you want to
lock the man up for?

30:46.540 --> 30:48.179
Man going down there,

30:48.260 --> 30:52.459
over there and fight that war,
messing with them Japs,

30:52.540 --> 30:54.213
getting half his head blown off.

30:54.300 --> 30:58.010
They give him a lousy $3,000.
I got to swoop down on that.

30:58.100 --> 30:59.420
Is you fixing to
get into that again?

30:59.500 --> 31:01.537
He got a metal plate in his head.

31:01.660 --> 31:03.697
That's the only reason I
got a roof over my head

31:03.780 --> 31:05.294
is 'cause of that metal plate.

31:05.380 --> 31:07.212
Ain't no sense in you
blaming yourself for nothing.

31:07.300 --> 31:09.496
Gabe was in no condition
to manage that money.

31:09.580 --> 31:10.696
You done what was right by him.

31:10.780 --> 31:12.817
Can't nobody say you ain't
done what was right by him.

31:12.900 --> 31:14.254
Look how long you took care of him.

31:14.380 --> 31:16.975
Till he wanted his own place and
moved over there with Miss Pearl.

31:17.060 --> 31:19.575
That ain't what I'm saying, woman.
I'm just...

31:22.180 --> 31:23.614
I'm just stating the facts.

31:23.700 --> 31:25.771
If my brother didn't have
a metal plate in his head,

31:25.860 --> 31:27.294
I wouldn't have a pot to piss in

31:27.380 --> 31:28.780
or a window to throw it out of.

31:28.860 --> 31:30.579
And I'm 53...

31:40.580 --> 31:42.139
Where you going off to?

31:42.220 --> 31:43.893
You been running out of here
every Saturday for weeks.

31:43.980 --> 31:46.814
I thought you were gonna
work on this fence.

31:46.900 --> 31:49.131
I'm gonna go down
to Taylors' and...

32:38.660 --> 32:39.650
Mama?

32:41.340 --> 32:43.900
Cory. Your daddy like
to have a fit with you

32:43.980 --> 32:46.859
running out of here this morning
without doing your chores.

32:46.940 --> 32:48.215
You all right?

32:48.300 --> 32:51.577
He say you supposed to be
helping him with the fence.

32:51.660 --> 32:53.060
I told you I had to go to practice.

32:53.140 --> 32:55.132
And he's been saying that the
last four or five Saturdays,

32:55.220 --> 32:58.292
and then don't ever do nothing
but go down to Taylors'.

32:59.740 --> 33:01.811
- You told him about the recruiter?
- Yeah, I told him.

33:01.900 --> 33:04.540
- Well, what'd he say?
- He didn't say nothing too much.

33:04.620 --> 33:07.260
Go on and get started on your
chores before he gets back here.

33:07.340 --> 33:09.980
Go on and scrub down them steps

33:10.060 --> 33:12.939
before he come back here
hollering and carrying on!

33:13.020 --> 33:14.852
Go! Boy, go!

33:37.460 --> 33:40.771
Go on, Troy.
You liked to scare me to death.

33:40.900 --> 33:42.050
What was the score of the game?

33:42.140 --> 33:43.972
Lucille had me on the phone.
I couldn't keep up with it.

33:44.060 --> 33:45.574
What do I care about the game?
Come here, woman.

33:45.660 --> 33:46.810
I thought you went down to Taylors'

33:46.900 --> 33:48.653
to listen to the game. Go on, Troy.

33:48.740 --> 33:50.459
I thought you're supposed
to be putting up the fence.

33:50.540 --> 33:52.896
I'll put it up when
I finish with what...

33:54.220 --> 33:55.336
Is at hand.

33:55.420 --> 33:57.491
Go on, Troy. I ain't studying you!

33:57.580 --> 34:00.493
I'm studying you.
I'm finna do my homework.

34:00.580 --> 34:02.253
Troy, you better leave me alone!

34:04.900 --> 34:06.493
Where Cory?
That boy brought his butt home yet?

34:06.580 --> 34:07.980
He's upstairs doing his chores.

34:08.060 --> 34:09.380
Cory, get your butt...

34:10.860 --> 34:13.056
- Where you going?
- I'll be right back.

34:13.139 --> 34:13.414
When?

34:13.484 --> 34:15.735
I'm just going right
down the street.

34:16.260 --> 34:19.571
Where? Who?

34:22.420 --> 34:24.092
Troy, go in the house!

34:52.300 --> 34:54.178
You just now coming here
from leaving this morning?

34:54.260 --> 34:55.121
Yeah,
I had to go to football practice...

34:55.190 --> 34:55.534
Yeah, what?

34:55.620 --> 34:56.610
Yes, sir.

34:56.699 --> 34:58.180
I ain't but two seconds off you,
no way.

34:58.260 --> 34:59.933
That garbage sitting in there,
overflowing.

35:00.020 --> 35:01.295
You ain't done none of your chores.

35:01.380 --> 35:02.575
Now you come in here,
talking about, "Yeah."

35:02.660 --> 35:04.094
I was just getting ready
to do my chores now, Pop.

35:04.180 --> 35:06.411
Your first chore is to help me
with this fence on Saturday.

35:06.500 --> 35:08.059
Everything else come after that.

35:08.140 --> 35:10.450
Now, get that saw,
we gonna cut these boards.

35:14.100 --> 35:17.571
Hey, Pop. Why don't you buy a TV?

35:17.660 --> 35:20.095
What I want with a TV?
What I want one of them for?

35:20.180 --> 35:22.979
Everybody got one.
Earl, Ba Bra, Jesse.

35:23.460 --> 35:25.258
I ain't asked who had one,
I said what I want with one?

35:25.380 --> 35:27.815
So, you can watch it.
They got lots of things on TV.

35:27.900 --> 35:29.129
- Baseball and everything.
- Yeah?

35:29.260 --> 35:30.535
We could watch the World Series.

35:30.620 --> 35:32.577
- Yeah, how much this TV cost?
- I don't know.

35:32.660 --> 35:35.255
They got 'em on sale for about $200.

35:35.340 --> 35:36.979
- $200?
- That ain't that much, Pop.

35:37.340 --> 35:39.650
No, that's just $200.

35:40.780 --> 35:42.851
You see that roof you got
sitting over your head at night?

35:43.140 --> 35:45.052
Let me tell you something
about that roof.

35:45.140 --> 35:49.020
It's been 10 years since
that roof was last tarred.

35:49.100 --> 35:52.218
See, now snow come this winter,
sit up on that roof like it is,

35:52.300 --> 35:54.257
it's gonna seep inside,
just gonna be a little bit,

35:54.340 --> 35:56.656
you ain't gonna hardly notice it,
then next thing you know,

35:56.740 --> 35:58.220
it's gonna be leaking
all over the house.

35:58.300 --> 36:00.245
Then the wood rot
from all that water,

36:00.315 --> 36:02.260
and you gonna need
a whole new roof.

36:02.340 --> 36:04.536
Now how much you think it
cost to get that roof fixed?

36:04.900 --> 36:08.860
- I don't know.
- $264 cash money. See?

36:08.940 --> 36:10.659
While you be thinking about a TV,

36:10.740 --> 36:12.698
I got to be thinking about the roof

36:12.768 --> 36:14.893
or whatever else go
wrong around here.

36:14.980 --> 36:16.892
Now if you had $200,
what would you do?

36:16.980 --> 36:19.370
Fix the roof, or buy a TV?

36:19.460 --> 36:21.850
I'd buy a TV.
And when the roof started to leak,

36:21.980 --> 36:23.255
if it needed fixing, I'd fix it.

36:23.340 --> 36:24.694
Where you gonna get your money from?

36:24.780 --> 36:26.100
You done spent it on a TV.

36:26.180 --> 36:27.396
You gonna sit up in there,

36:27.466 --> 36:29.571
let that water run all
over your brand-new TV?

36:29.660 --> 36:31.219
Pop, you got the money.
I know you do.

36:31.300 --> 36:33.019
- Where I got it at?
- In the bank.

36:33.100 --> 36:34.375
You want to see my bank book?

36:34.460 --> 36:37.259
You want to see that $73.22
I got sitting up in there?

36:37.340 --> 36:39.013
You don't have to pay
for it all at one time.

36:39.100 --> 36:40.978
You can put a down payment on it,
and carry it on with you.

36:41.060 --> 36:43.734
Not me. I ain't owing nobody
nothing if I can help it.

36:43.820 --> 36:46.380
Miss a payment, they come and
snatch it right out of your house.

36:46.460 --> 36:49.498
Then what you got? See?

36:49.580 --> 36:53.096
Now, when I get $200 clear,
I'll buy me a TV.

36:53.220 --> 36:56.577
Right now, when I get $264,
I'm gonna get that roof fixed.

36:56.660 --> 36:57.650
Pop...

36:57.740 --> 37:00.460
You go get you $200 and buy
you a TV if you want to.

37:00.540 --> 37:02.133
I got better things
to do with my money.

37:02.220 --> 37:04.451
I can't get $200.
I ain't never seen $200.

37:04.860 --> 37:06.089
All right, I'll tell you what.

37:06.180 --> 37:09.378
You get $100,
I'll put the other $100 with it.

37:09.460 --> 37:10.940
All right, I'm gonna show you.

37:11.020 --> 37:14.252
Yeah, show me how you can
cut these boards right now.

37:14.980 --> 37:17.415
There you go. That's $200 worth.

37:20.180 --> 37:21.933
- The Pirates won today.
- Yeah?

37:22.020 --> 37:23.136
That makes five in a row.

37:23.220 --> 37:25.655
I ain't thinking about no Pirates.
They got an all-white team.

37:25.740 --> 37:29.416
Got that boy, though,
that Puerto Rican boy, Clemente?

37:29.740 --> 37:30.810
Don't even half play him.

37:30.900 --> 37:32.892
That boy could be something
if they'd give him a chance.

37:33.140 --> 37:35.018
Play him one day,
sit him on the bench the next.

37:35.100 --> 37:36.329
He gets lots of chances to play.

37:36.420 --> 37:38.332
I'm talking about playing every day,
playing regular,

37:38.420 --> 37:39.979
so you can get your timing,
that's what I'm talking about.

37:40.100 --> 37:42.171
They got some white guys on the
team that don't play every day.

37:42.260 --> 37:43.489
You can't play everybody
at the same time.

37:43.580 --> 37:45.378
If they got a white fellow
sitting on the bench,

37:45.460 --> 37:48.100
you can bet your last
dollar he can't play.

37:48.180 --> 37:50.217
Colored guy got to be twice
as good to get on the team.

37:50.300 --> 37:53.099
That's why I don't want you
getting all tied up in them sports.

37:53.180 --> 37:55.217
Man on the team, what it get him?

37:55.300 --> 37:57.257
Got colored on the team,
don't even use him.

37:57.340 --> 38:00.094
Same as not having them.
All them teams the same.

38:00.180 --> 38:02.456
The Braves got Hank
Aaron and Wes Covington.

38:02.580 --> 38:04.572
Hank Aaron hit two home runs today.
That makes 43.

38:04.660 --> 38:06.617
Aaron ain't nobody.
That's what you supposed to do.

38:06.700 --> 38:08.498
That's how the game's
supposed to be played.

38:08.580 --> 38:09.287
Ain't nothing to it.

38:09.357 --> 38:11.300
It's a matter of getting your
timing and follow through.

38:11.420 --> 38:13.537
Hell,
I can hit 43 home runs right now.

38:13.620 --> 38:15.100
Not off no major-league pitcher,
you couldn't.

38:15.180 --> 38:16.739
We had better pitching
in the Negro leagues.

38:16.820 --> 38:18.573
I hit seven home runs
off of Satchel Paige.

38:18.660 --> 38:19.889
You can't get no better than that.

38:19.980 --> 38:21.653
Sandy Koufax,
he leading the league in strikeouts.

38:21.740 --> 38:23.254
I ain't thinking
about no Sandy Koufax.

38:23.340 --> 38:25.093
You got Warren Spahn and
Lew Burdette. I bet you...

38:25.180 --> 38:26.409
I'm through with it now.

38:30.660 --> 38:33.050
Go and cut them boards.

38:35.180 --> 38:38.457
Your mama told me you got recruited
by a college football team.

38:38.540 --> 38:39.860
Is that right?

38:40.060 --> 38:41.663
Yeah, Coach Zellman
say the recruiter

38:41.733 --> 38:43.292
gonna be coming
by to talk to you.

38:43.380 --> 38:45.417
Get you to sign the
permission papers.

38:45.540 --> 38:47.099
I thought you was supposed
to be working down the A&P.

38:47.180 --> 38:48.819
Ain't you supposed to be
working down there after school?

38:48.900 --> 38:50.653
Mr. Stawicki say he
gonna hold my job for me

38:50.740 --> 38:52.140
until after the football season.

38:52.420 --> 38:54.810
He said starting next week,
I can work weekends.

38:54.900 --> 38:55.081
Boy,

38:55.151 --> 38:57.813
I thought we had an understanding
about this football stuff.

38:57.900 --> 38:59.619
You supposed to keep
up with your chores,

38:59.700 --> 39:01.498
hold your job down
there at the A&P.

39:01.580 --> 39:03.776
You ain't been around here
all day on a Saturday,

39:03.860 --> 39:05.135
ain't none of your chores done.

39:05.220 --> 39:06.893
Now you come telling me
you done quit your job?

39:07.020 --> 39:09.057
- I'm gonna be working weekends.
- You damn right you are!

39:09.140 --> 39:10.972
And ain't no need for nobody
to be coming around here,

39:11.060 --> 39:12.210
talking to me about signing nothing.

39:12.300 --> 39:13.336
Pop, you can't do that.

39:13.420 --> 39:14.695
He's coming all the way
from North Carolina.

39:14.820 --> 39:16.652
I don't care where he coming from!

39:16.780 --> 39:17.930
Look, boy,

39:19.060 --> 39:20.460
the white man ain't gonna let you

39:20.540 --> 39:22.338
get nowhere with no football no way.

39:22.740 --> 39:24.936
Now you get your book-learning,
so you can

39:25.060 --> 39:27.973
work your way up at the A&P
and learn how to fix cars,

39:28.060 --> 39:29.733
or build houses, get you a trade.

39:29.820 --> 39:32.335
This way, you got something
can't nobody take away from you.

39:32.460 --> 39:34.850
You go in and learn how to
put your hands to good use

39:34.940 --> 39:36.818
besides hauling other
people's garbage.

39:36.900 --> 39:37.970
I get good grades, Pop.

39:38.060 --> 39:39.414
That's why the recruiter
want to talk with you.

39:39.500 --> 39:41.059
You got to keep up your
grades to get recruited.

39:41.140 --> 39:42.972
This way, I'll be going to college,
I'll get a chance.

39:43.060 --> 39:46.531
First, you get your butt down
there and get your job back.

39:46.620 --> 39:48.054
Mr. Stawicki done already
hired somebody else

39:48.140 --> 39:49.574
'cause I told him I
was playing football.

39:51.220 --> 39:53.052
You a bigger fool than I thought.

39:53.140 --> 39:55.132
You gonna let somebody
take away your job,

39:55.220 --> 39:56.540
so you can play some football.

39:57.100 --> 39:58.222
Where you gonna get your money

39:58.292 --> 39:59.900
to take care of your
girlfriend and whatnot?

39:59.980 --> 40:01.334
What kind of foolishness is that

40:01.420 --> 40:02.854
to let somebody take away your job?

40:02.940 --> 40:04.169
I'm still gonna be
working weekends.

40:04.260 --> 40:06.331
No. You getting out of here
and finding you another job.

40:06.420 --> 40:07.695
Come on, Pop. I gotta practice.

40:07.780 --> 40:09.533
I can't work after school
and play football, too.

40:09.620 --> 40:11.179
The team needs me,
that's what Coach Zellman say.

40:11.260 --> 40:13.411
I don't care what nobody say.
I'm the boss. You understand?

40:13.500 --> 40:16.732
I'm the boss around here.
I do the only saying what counts.

40:16.820 --> 40:19.210
- Come on...
- I asked you, "Do you understand?"

40:19.340 --> 40:22.219
- Yeah.
- What?

40:22.300 --> 40:25.452
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

40:25.540 --> 40:26.935
You get on down
there to that A&P

40:27.005 --> 40:28.570
and see if you can
get your job back.

40:28.660 --> 40:31.220
If you can't do both,
then you quit the football team.

40:31.300 --> 40:33.417
You got to take the
crookeds with the straights.

40:33.500 --> 40:34.695
Yes, sir.

40:42.300 --> 40:45.372
- Can I ask you a question?
- What the hell you got to ask me?

40:45.460 --> 40:48.259
Mr. Stawicki the one you
got the questions for.

40:48.340 --> 40:49.820
How come you ain't never liked me?

40:51.020 --> 40:55.253
Like you?
Who the hell said I got to like you?

40:56.740 --> 40:58.891
What law is there say
I got to like you?

40:58.980 --> 41:00.413
You want to stand up
in front of my face

41:00.483 --> 41:02.099
and ask a damn fool-ass
question like that.

41:02.180 --> 41:03.455
Talk about liking somebody.

41:03.540 --> 41:04.860
Come here, boy, when I talk to you.

41:07.220 --> 41:11.499
Straighten up, God damn it!
I asked you a question.

41:11.780 --> 41:14.079
What law is there
say I got to like you?

41:14.149 --> 41:14.739
None.

41:14.820 --> 41:16.812
All right, then.
Don't you eat every day?

41:18.180 --> 41:19.614
Answer me when I talk to you.

41:19.700 --> 41:20.736
- Don't you eat every day?
- Yeah.

41:20.860 --> 41:22.533
Nigger, as long as you in my house,

41:22.620 --> 41:24.612
you put a "sir" on the end
of it when you talk to me.

41:24.740 --> 41:26.094
- Yes, sir.
- You eat every day?

41:26.180 --> 41:27.500
- Got a roof over your head?
- Yes, sir.

41:27.580 --> 41:28.775
- Got clothes on your back?
- Yes, sir.

41:28.860 --> 41:30.340
- Why you think that is?
- 'Cause of you.

41:31.060 --> 41:35.020
Hell, I know it's 'cause of me.
But why do you think that is?

41:36.700 --> 41:38.020
'Cause you like me?

41:38.220 --> 41:40.132
"Like" you.

41:40.220 --> 41:42.098
I go out of here every morning,

41:42.180 --> 41:45.491
I bust my butt putting up
with them crackers every day

41:45.580 --> 41:47.299
'cause I "like" you.

41:47.380 --> 41:50.418
You about the biggest fool
I ever saw. It's my job.

41:50.500 --> 41:52.332
It's my responsibility.

41:52.420 --> 41:55.219
A man is supposed to
take care of his family.

41:55.420 --> 41:58.299
You live in my house,
fill your belly with my food,

41:58.380 --> 42:01.976
put your behind on my bed
because you're my son.

42:02.060 --> 42:04.859
Not 'cause I like you. 'Cause
it's my duty to take care of you.

42:04.940 --> 42:07.500
I owe a responsibility to you.

42:07.580 --> 42:09.458
Now, let's get this
straight right here and now,

42:09.540 --> 42:11.099
before it go along any further.

42:11.180 --> 42:12.660
I ain't got to like you.

42:12.740 --> 42:15.858
Mr. Rand don't give me my money
come payday 'cause he like me.

42:15.940 --> 42:18.978
He give it to me 'cause he owe me.

42:19.460 --> 42:21.099
Now I done give you
everything I got to give you.

42:21.180 --> 42:23.490
I give you your life!

42:23.580 --> 42:25.060
Me and your mama worked
that out between us,

42:25.140 --> 42:28.258
and liking your black ass
wasn't part of the bargain.

42:28.460 --> 42:29.860
Now don't you go through life

42:29.940 --> 42:32.171
worrying about whether
somebody like you, or not.

42:32.260 --> 42:35.332
You best be making sure
they're doing right by you.

42:35.420 --> 42:37.059
- You understand what I'm saying?
- Yes, sir.

42:37.140 --> 42:40.577
Then get the hell out of my face
and get on down to that A&P!

43:03.940 --> 43:06.375
Why don't you go ahead and let
the boy play football, Troy?

43:06.460 --> 43:08.372
He just want to be like
you with the sports.

43:08.460 --> 43:10.531
I don't want him to be like me.

43:10.620 --> 43:12.213
I want him to get as
far away from my life

43:12.300 --> 43:13.370
as he possibly can get.

43:13.460 --> 43:15.611
You the only decent thing
ever happened to me, Rose.

43:16.140 --> 43:17.574
And I wish him that.

43:18.140 --> 43:21.292
But I don't wish him
nothing else from my life.

43:22.300 --> 43:23.563
I decided 17 years ago,

43:23.633 --> 43:26.214
that boy wasn't gonna get
involved in no sports.

43:26.300 --> 43:27.939
Not after what they did
to me in the sports.

43:28.020 --> 43:30.251
Why don't you just admit you were
too old for the major leagues?

43:30.340 --> 43:31.933
For once,
why don't you just admit that?

43:32.020 --> 43:33.693
Don't you come tellin'
me I was too old.

43:33.780 --> 43:37.012
I just wasn't the right color.
Hell, I'm 53 years old,

43:37.140 --> 43:40.212
I can do better than
Selkirk's .269 right now.

43:40.300 --> 43:42.656
How were you gonna play
ball when you were over 40?

43:42.740 --> 43:44.413
Sometimes,
I can't get no sense out of you.

43:44.500 --> 43:45.570
I got good sense, woman.

43:45.660 --> 43:48.892
I got sense enough not to let that
boy get hurt playing no sports.

43:48.980 --> 43:50.494
You mothering the boy too much.

43:50.620 --> 43:52.737
Worrying about whether people
"like" him or not.

43:52.820 --> 43:56.097
Everything that boy do,
he do for you.

43:56.180 --> 43:58.048
He wants you to say,
"Good job, son."

43:58.118 --> 43:58.740
That's all.

43:59.180 --> 44:02.298
I ain't got time for that, Rose.
He's alive, he's healthy.

44:02.380 --> 44:05.737
He's got to make his own way.
I made mine.

44:05.860 --> 44:08.375
Ain't nobody gonna hold his hand
when he get out there in the world.

44:08.460 --> 44:10.816
Times have changed, Troy.

44:10.900 --> 44:12.971
People change.

44:13.060 --> 44:15.336
The world changing,
and you can't even see it.

44:21.860 --> 44:24.614
Woman, I do the best I can do.

44:24.700 --> 44:26.020
I come in here every Friday,

44:26.100 --> 44:28.934
I carry a sack of potatoes
and a bucket of lard.

44:29.020 --> 44:32.616
You all line up at the
door with your hands out.

44:32.700 --> 44:36.296
I give you the lint from my pockets.
I give you my sweat and my blood.

44:36.380 --> 44:38.975
I ain't got no tears.
I done spent them.

44:39.100 --> 44:41.695
We go upstairs in that room
at night, I fall down on you

44:41.780 --> 44:45.296
and try to blast a
hole into forever.

44:45.380 --> 44:47.611
I get up Monday morning,
find my lunch on the table,

44:47.700 --> 44:49.100
go out and make my way.

44:49.180 --> 44:53.459
Find my strength to get
me through to next Friday.

44:53.540 --> 44:54.940
That's all I got, Rose.

44:58.060 --> 45:00.859
That's all I got to give.

45:05.060 --> 45:06.574
Can't give nothing else!

45:33.500 --> 45:34.775
Mr. Maxson?

45:37.700 --> 45:39.896
Commissioner will see you now.

45:46.700 --> 45:48.054
Rose!

45:51.020 --> 45:52.613
Hey, Ro!

45:52.700 --> 45:57.092
I wish I could've seen Mr.
Rand's face when he told you.

45:57.220 --> 45:59.974
He couldn't get it out his mouth.
Liked to bit his tongue.

46:00.060 --> 46:01.972
When they called me down there
to the Commissioner's office,

46:02.100 --> 46:04.854
he thought they was gonna fire me,
like everybody else.

46:04.940 --> 46:06.579
I didn't think they
was gonna fire you.

46:06.660 --> 46:09.129
I thought they's gonna put
you on the warning paper.

46:09.220 --> 46:12.531
Hey, Rose! Yeah,
Mr. Rand liked to bit his tongue.

46:12.620 --> 46:14.657
I see you run right
down there to Taylors'

46:14.780 --> 46:16.055
and told that Alberta gal.

46:16.140 --> 46:19.212
Hey, Rose!
I told everybody. Hey, Ro!

46:19.300 --> 46:21.212
I went down there to cash my check.

46:22.100 --> 46:23.136
Hey!

46:23.220 --> 46:25.018
Hush all that hollering.
I know you out here.

46:25.100 --> 46:26.898
What they say down at the
Commissioner's office?

46:26.980 --> 46:28.778
You supposed to come
when I call you, woman.

46:28.860 --> 46:30.010
Bono will tell you that.

46:30.100 --> 46:31.614
Don't Lucille come
when you call her?

46:31.700 --> 46:32.816
Man, hush your mouth.
I ain't no dog.

46:32.900 --> 46:34.220
Talk about come when you call me.

46:34.340 --> 46:35.854
You hear this, Bono?
I used to have me an old dog

46:35.940 --> 46:37.010
get uppity like that.

46:37.100 --> 46:39.660
You say, "Come here, Blue,"
he just lay there, look at you.

46:39.740 --> 46:41.971
End up getting a stick chasin'
him away, trying to make him come.

46:42.100 --> 46:43.580
I ain't studying you and your dog.

46:43.660 --> 46:45.253
I remember you used
to sing that old song.

46:45.500 --> 46:47.651
<i>Hear it ring! Hear it ring!</i>

46:47.860 --> 46:49.533
<i>Had an old dog, his name was Blue</i>

46:49.620 --> 46:51.134
Nobody wants to hear that old song.

46:52.100 --> 46:53.853
<i>You know Blue was mighty true</i>

46:53.940 --> 46:56.011
Used to have Cory runnin'
around here singin' that song.

46:56.100 --> 46:57.773
Hell, I remember that song myself.

46:57.860 --> 47:00.216
<i>You know Blue was a good old dog</i>

47:00.420 --> 47:02.616
<i>Blue treed a possum in a hollow log</i>

47:02.780 --> 47:05.295
That's my daddy's song.
My daddy made up that song.

47:05.380 --> 47:07.940
I don't care who made it up. Don't
nobody want to hear you sing it.

47:08.260 --> 47:09.614
<i>Come here, woman!</i>

47:09.940 --> 47:13.411
You come in here carrying on,
I reckon they ain't fired you.

47:13.500 --> 47:15.457
What they say down there at
the Commissioner's office?

47:15.540 --> 47:18.578
Look here, Rose.
Mr. Rand called me in his office

47:18.660 --> 47:21.175
after I got back from talkin'
to them people down there.

47:21.260 --> 47:23.570
He called me in his
office and told me...

47:25.300 --> 47:26.700
They was making me a driver!

47:27.300 --> 47:30.213
- Troy, you kidding!
- No, I ain't. Ask Bono.

47:30.300 --> 47:32.934
That's great, Troy. Now you don't
have to hassle them people no more.

47:33.020 --> 47:36.138
Oh, hell. I didn't think
I was gonna see you today.

47:36.220 --> 47:37.700
I thought you was in jail.

47:37.820 --> 47:40.130
Got it all over the <i>Courier</i>
about them raiding Seefus' place

47:40.220 --> 47:42.735
where you be hanging
out with all them thugs.

47:42.820 --> 47:44.459
Hey, Pop, that ain't got
nothing to do with me.

47:44.660 --> 47:45.855
I don't go down there gambling.

47:45.940 --> 47:47.818
I just go down there to
sit in with the band.

47:47.900 --> 47:49.971
I ain't got nothing to do
with the gambling part.

47:50.060 --> 47:51.574
They got some good music down there.

47:51.660 --> 47:53.413
They got some rogues
is what they got.

47:53.500 --> 47:55.492
How you been, Mr. Bono? Hi, Rose.

47:55.580 --> 47:58.220
I see where you playing down
at the Crawford Grill tonight.

47:58.340 --> 47:59.820
How come you ain't brought
Bonnie like I told you?

47:59.900 --> 48:00.890
You shoulda brought Bonnie.

48:00.980 --> 48:02.300
She ain't been by in
a month of Sundays.

48:02.380 --> 48:03.575
I was just in the neighborhood.

48:03.660 --> 48:05.060
- Thought I'd stop by.
- Here it comes.

48:05.180 --> 48:07.376
Your daddy got a
promotion on the rubbish.

48:07.460 --> 48:09.770
He gonna be the
first colored driver.

48:09.860 --> 48:11.140
Ain't got to do nothin'
but sit up there

48:11.210 --> 48:12.654
and read the paper,
like them white fellas.

48:12.740 --> 48:15.460
Hey, Pop, if you knew how to read,
you'd be all right.

48:15.540 --> 48:18.055
Nah, nah. You mean if the
nigger knew how to drive,

48:18.140 --> 48:19.256
he'd be all right.

48:19.500 --> 48:21.457
Been fighting with them
people about driving

48:21.527 --> 48:22.893
and ain't even got a license.

48:22.980 --> 48:24.699
Mr. Rand know you ain't
got no driver's license?

48:24.780 --> 48:25.770
Driving ain't nothing.

48:25.860 --> 48:27.613
All you do is point the truck
where you want it to go.

48:27.700 --> 48:28.770
Driving ain't nothing.

48:28.860 --> 48:30.374
Do they know you ain't
got no driver's license?

48:30.500 --> 48:31.570
That's what I'm talkin' about.

48:31.660 --> 48:33.014
I ain't asked if driving was easy.

48:33.100 --> 48:35.456
I asked if Mr. Rand know you
ain't got no driver's license.

48:35.540 --> 48:36.610
The man ain't got
to know my business.

48:36.700 --> 48:38.851
Time he find out, I have two or
three of them driver's license.

48:38.940 --> 48:40.818
- Say, look here, Pop.
- I knew it was coming.

48:40.900 --> 48:42.812
I knew what kinda "Look here,
Pop" that was.

48:42.900 --> 48:44.220
Nigger finna ask me for some money.

48:44.460 --> 48:46.179
It's Friday night, it's my payday.

48:46.260 --> 48:49.776
All them rogues down on the avenue,
the ones that ain't in jail,

48:49.860 --> 48:52.580
and Lyons is hopping in his shoes
to get down there with them.

48:52.660 --> 48:53.696
Now, see, Pop,

48:53.780 --> 48:56.295
if you gave somebody else
a chance to talk sometime,

48:56.380 --> 48:59.976
you'd see I was fixing to pay you
back your $10 like I told you.

49:00.060 --> 49:03.212
Here. I told you I'd pay
you when Bonnie got paid.

49:03.300 --> 49:05.496
No, you keep that $10.
Put it in the bank.

49:05.580 --> 49:07.173
Next time you feel like
you wanna come by here

49:07.260 --> 49:08.899
and ask me for somethin',
you go down there and get that.

49:09.220 --> 49:10.449
Here you go your $10, Pop.

49:10.580 --> 49:12.333
I told you,
I don't want you to give me nothing.

49:12.420 --> 49:13.649
I just wanted to borrow $10.

49:13.740 --> 49:16.300
No, you keep that for the
next time you want to ask me.

49:16.580 --> 49:17.900
Come on, Pop, here go your $10.

49:17.980 --> 49:21.052
Troy, why don't you let
the boy pay you back?

49:23.900 --> 49:26.460
Here you go, Rose.
If you don't take it,

49:26.540 --> 49:28.497
I'm gonna hear about it
for the next six months.

49:28.580 --> 49:30.219
You can hand yours over, too, Troy.

49:30.300 --> 49:31.814
You see this, Bono?
You see how they do me?

49:31.900 --> 49:33.653
Yeah, Lucille do me the same way.

49:33.780 --> 49:37.091
<i>Better get ready for the Judgment</i>

49:38.580 --> 49:40.139
<i>Better get ready</i>

49:42.940 --> 49:44.932
Hey. Hey, there's Troy's boy!

49:45.020 --> 49:46.340
How you doing, Uncle Gabe?

49:46.420 --> 49:47.900
Lyons!

49:49.860 --> 49:52.216
The King of the Jungle!

49:52.620 --> 49:55.499
Rose.
Hey, Rose, I got a flower for you.

49:55.580 --> 49:58.015
I picked it myself.
That's the same rose like you is.

49:58.100 --> 49:59.773
That's right nice of you, Gabe.

49:59.860 --> 50:01.374
What you been doing, Uncle Gabe?

50:01.460 --> 50:04.931
I been chasing hellhounds
and waiting for the time

50:05.020 --> 50:06.852
to tell Saint Peter
to open the Gates.

50:06.940 --> 50:08.613
You been chasing hellhounds, huh?

50:08.700 --> 50:10.419
Well, you doing the right thing,
Uncle Gabe.

50:10.500 --> 50:13.493
- Somebody's got to chase 'em.
- Yeah, I know it.

50:13.580 --> 50:16.459
The devil's strong.
The devil ain't no pushover.

50:16.540 --> 50:18.975
Hellhounds snipping
at everybody's heels.

50:19.060 --> 50:21.655
But I got my trumpet waiting
on the Judgment time.

50:21.740 --> 50:23.459
Waiting on the Battle of Armageddon,
huh?

50:23.540 --> 50:25.611
Ain't gonna be too much of a battle

50:25.740 --> 50:29.177
when God get to waving
that Judgment sword.

50:29.260 --> 50:31.331
But the people's gonna
have a hell of a time

50:31.420 --> 50:33.980
trying to get into Heaven
if them Gates ain't open.

50:34.060 --> 50:35.574
You hear this, Pop?

50:36.140 --> 50:38.336
- Uncle Gabe, you all right.
- Lyons.

50:41.460 --> 50:43.895
- The King of the Jungle!
- You stayin' for supper, Gabe?

50:43.980 --> 50:45.050
You want me to fix you a plate?

50:45.140 --> 50:48.053
I'll just take a sandwich, Rose.
I don't want no plate.

50:48.140 --> 50:50.257
I want to eat with my hands.
I'll take a sandwich.

50:50.340 --> 50:52.730
What about you, Lyons? You stayin'?
Got some short ribs cooking.

50:52.820 --> 50:56.291
Nah. I won't eat nothing
till after we finish playing.

50:56.940 --> 50:58.932
You ought to come down,
listen to me play, Pop.

50:59.020 --> 51:01.296
I don't like all that Chinese music,
all that noise.

51:01.380 --> 51:04.851
Go in there and wash up, Gabe.
I'll fix you a sandwich.

51:04.940 --> 51:07.580
Troy mad at me.

51:07.660 --> 51:09.014
What you mad at Uncle Gabe for?

51:09.100 --> 51:11.934
He think Troy mad at him 'cause he
moved over there to Miss Pearl's.

51:12.020 --> 51:14.091
I ain't mad at the man.
He can live where he want to live at.

51:14.180 --> 51:16.331
Well, what he move over there for?
Miss Pearl don't like nobody.

51:16.420 --> 51:18.173
She don't mind him none.
She treat him real nice.

51:18.260 --> 51:19.740
She just don't allow
all that singing.

51:19.820 --> 51:22.380
She don't mind that rent he be
paying. That's what she don't mind.

51:22.460 --> 51:23.974
Troy, I ain't goin'
through that with you no more.

51:24.060 --> 51:25.858
He moved over there
'cause he wanted his own place.

51:25.940 --> 51:27.010
He can come and go as he please.

51:27.100 --> 51:28.349
He can come and go
as he please here.

51:28.419 --> 51:29.217
I wasn't stoppin' him.

51:29.300 --> 51:30.529
I wasn't putting no
rules on the man.

51:30.620 --> 51:32.373
That ain't the same thing,
and you know it.

51:32.460 --> 51:33.689
Now that's the last I
wanna hear about that.

51:33.780 --> 51:35.931
I don't wanna hear nothin'
else about Gabe and Miss Pearl.

51:36.060 --> 51:38.700
- And next week...
- I'm ready for my sandwich, Rose.

51:38.780 --> 51:40.931
And next week, when that
recruiter come from that school,

51:41.020 --> 51:43.694
I want you to sign that paper and
go on and let Cory play football.

51:43.780 --> 51:45.499
That'll be the last I
have to hear about that.

51:50.180 --> 51:52.172
Cory got recruited?
What school he goin' to?

51:52.300 --> 51:53.893
I ain't thinking about Cory nothing.

51:53.980 --> 51:55.805
Boy walking around here
smelling his piss,

51:55.875 --> 51:57.700
thinking he gonna do
what he want to do,

51:57.780 --> 52:00.056
irregardless of what I say.

52:00.140 --> 52:02.416
Look here, Bono,
I left the Commissioner's office

52:02.500 --> 52:03.900
and went down to the A&P.

52:03.980 --> 52:06.176
That boy ain't workin' down there,
he lied to me.

52:06.260 --> 52:09.617
Tellin' me he got his job back,
tellin' me he workin' weekend,

52:09.700 --> 52:11.259
tellin' me he workin' after school.

52:11.340 --> 52:13.571
Mr. Stawicki says he ain't
working down there at all.

52:13.660 --> 52:14.855
Cory just growing up.

52:14.940 --> 52:16.977
He just bustin' at the seams,
tryin' to fill out your shoes.

52:17.100 --> 52:18.250
I don't care what he doing.

52:18.340 --> 52:20.411
When he get to the place
where he want to disobey me,

52:20.500 --> 52:23.652
then it's time for him to move on.
Bono will tell you that.

52:23.740 --> 52:25.693
I bet he ain't never
disobeyed his daddy

52:25.763 --> 52:27.416
without paying the consequences.

52:27.500 --> 52:29.776
I ain't never had the chance.

52:29.860 --> 52:33.456
My daddy came on through, but I
ain't never knew him to see him.

52:33.540 --> 52:36.135
Or what he had on his mind,
or where he went.

52:36.220 --> 52:39.896
Just moving on through.
Searching out the New Land.

52:40.780 --> 52:43.090
That's what the old
folks used to call it.

52:43.180 --> 52:46.617
See a fella moving around from
place to place, woman to woman,

52:46.700 --> 52:49.090
they call it
"Searching out the New Land."

52:49.180 --> 52:50.819
I can't say if he ever found it.

52:51.580 --> 52:54.049
I come along, didn't want no kids.

52:54.540 --> 52:56.532
I didn't know if I was gonna
be in one place long enough

52:56.620 --> 52:58.612
to fix on 'em right as their daddy.

52:58.700 --> 53:00.817
I figured I was going searching,
too.

53:00.900 --> 53:03.131
As it turn out,
I been hooked up with Lucille

53:03.220 --> 53:05.610
for near about as long as
your daddy been with Rose.

53:05.700 --> 53:07.851
Going on 16 years.

53:07.940 --> 53:09.818
Sometimes,
I wish I'd never known my daddy.

53:09.900 --> 53:11.941
He ain't cared
nothing about no kids.

53:12.011 --> 53:13.655
A kid to him wasn't nothing.

53:14.060 --> 53:17.212
All he wanted you to do
was learn how to walk,

53:17.300 --> 53:18.973
so he could start you to working.

53:19.060 --> 53:20.609
Come to eating, he ate first.

53:20.679 --> 53:22.815
Anything left over,
that's what you got.

53:22.900 --> 53:24.732
Man would sit down,
eat two chickens,

53:24.802 --> 53:25.972
and give you the wing.

53:26.060 --> 53:29.337
You ought to stop that, Pop.
Everybody feed their kids.

53:29.420 --> 53:32.538
No matter how hard times is,
everybody care about their kids.

53:32.620 --> 53:33.815
Make sure they have
something to eat.

53:33.900 --> 53:35.653
Only thing my daddy cared about

53:35.740 --> 53:37.493
was getting them bales of
cotton in to Mr. Lubin.

53:37.580 --> 53:39.617
That's the only thing
that mattered to him.

53:39.700 --> 53:41.851
Sometimes, I used to wonder
why he was still living,

53:41.940 --> 53:44.500
why the devil hadn't
come and got him.

53:44.740 --> 53:46.652
"Get them bales of
cotton in to Mr. Lubin."

53:46.740 --> 53:48.094
Find out he owe him money.

53:48.180 --> 53:50.376
He should have just went on and left
when he saw he couldn't get nowhere.

53:50.460 --> 53:51.496
That's what I would've done.

53:51.580 --> 53:54.493
How he gonna leave with 11 kids?
And where he gonna go?

53:54.580 --> 53:57.778
He ain't knew nothing but how
to farm. No, he was trapped.

53:58.180 --> 54:01.332
I think he knew it, too.
But I'll say this for him...

54:01.420 --> 54:03.173
He felt a responsibility toward us.

54:03.260 --> 54:05.252
May not have treated us
like I felt he should have,

54:05.340 --> 54:09.254
but without that responsibility,
he could have run off and left us,

54:09.380 --> 54:10.700
made his own way.

54:10.780 --> 54:12.180
A lot of them did.

54:12.260 --> 54:13.853
Back in those days,
what you talkin' about?

54:13.940 --> 54:15.579
They walk out their front door

54:15.660 --> 54:18.858
and take off down one road or
another and just keep on walkin'.

54:18.940 --> 54:20.852
There you go.
That's what I'm talkin' about.

54:20.940 --> 54:24.297
Just keep on walking till
they come to something else.

54:24.380 --> 54:27.691
Ain't you never heard of nobody
having the walking blues?

54:27.780 --> 54:30.249
Now, that's what you call it
when you just take off like that.

54:30.900 --> 54:34.211
My daddy ain't had no walking blues.
What you talking about?

54:34.300 --> 54:35.780
He stayed right there
with his family,

54:36.620 --> 54:40.534
but he was just as
evil as he could be!

54:40.660 --> 54:44.290
My mama couldn't stand him.
Couldn't stand that evilness.

54:44.380 --> 54:47.373
She run off when I was about eight.

54:47.500 --> 54:50.618
She sneaked off one night,
told me she was coming back for me.

54:50.700 --> 54:52.419
I ain't never seen her no more.

54:52.500 --> 54:56.619
All his women run off and left him.
He wasn't good for nobody.

54:57.140 --> 54:58.813
My turn come to head out.

54:58.900 --> 55:00.254
I was 14,

55:00.340 --> 55:03.219
got to sniffing around
Joe Canewell's daughter.

55:04.580 --> 55:06.890
We had this old mule called
"Greyboy".

55:07.020 --> 55:09.137
My daddy sent me out
to do some plowing.

55:09.220 --> 55:12.896
I got to fooling around with
Joe Canewell's daughter.

55:12.980 --> 55:16.178
Found us a nice spot,
got real cozy with each other.

55:16.260 --> 55:19.458
She was about 13,
so we done figured we grown anyway.

55:19.540 --> 55:21.930
So, we were down there by the creek,
enjoying ourselves,

55:22.020 --> 55:23.420
ain't thinking about nothing.

55:23.500 --> 55:25.810
Didn't know Greyboy
had gotten loose,

55:25.900 --> 55:29.337
wandered back to the house,
and my daddy was lookin' for me.

55:29.620 --> 55:33.091
So, we down there enjoying
ourselves when he come up on us.

55:33.180 --> 55:35.251
Surprised us.

55:35.380 --> 55:37.895
Had them leather
straps off that mule,

55:37.980 --> 55:41.018
commenced to whupping me
like there was no tomorrow.

55:41.100 --> 55:43.695
I jump up. I'm mad, embarrassed.

55:44.380 --> 55:46.497
I was scared of my daddy.

55:46.700 --> 55:48.692
Now,
when he commenced to whipping on me,

55:48.780 --> 55:50.499
quite naturally,
I run to get out of the way.

55:50.580 --> 55:53.254
Now, I think he's mad
'cause I ain't done my work.

55:53.340 --> 55:57.971
But I see where he's chasing me off,
so he can have the gal for himself.

55:59.380 --> 56:01.497
When I see what the
matter of it was,

56:02.380 --> 56:06.659
I lost all fear of my daddy,
and right there, I became a man.

56:06.740 --> 56:09.130
Fourteen years of age.

56:09.220 --> 56:12.133
Now, it's my turn to run him off.

56:12.220 --> 56:14.018
I picked up them same
reins he used on me.

56:14.100 --> 56:17.696
I picked up them reins,
I commenced to whupping on him.

56:18.740 --> 56:21.050
Gal jump up, she run off.

56:22.980 --> 56:24.209
When he turned to face me,

56:24.300 --> 56:26.178
I knew why the devil
never come and get him

56:26.260 --> 56:28.411
'cause he was the devil himself.

56:29.740 --> 56:32.300
I don't know what happened.

56:32.380 --> 56:35.578
I woke up,
laying there by the creek,

56:35.660 --> 56:39.336
and Blue, this old dog we had,
he was licking my face.

56:39.420 --> 56:42.458
Both my eyes were swoll shut.

56:42.540 --> 56:44.372
I thought I was blind,
I couldn't see nothing.

56:44.460 --> 56:48.170
I just laid there and cried.

56:53.740 --> 56:56.653
And I didn't know
what I was gonna do.

56:56.740 --> 57:01.178
But I knew the time had come for
me to leave my daddy's house.

57:02.460 --> 57:04.770
Suddenly, the world got big, and...

57:07.860 --> 57:10.209
It was a long time before
I could cut it down

57:10.279 --> 57:11.774
to where I could handle it.

57:13.460 --> 57:16.294
Part of that cutting down
was where I got to the place

57:16.380 --> 57:18.372
where I could feel him
kicking in my blood,

57:18.460 --> 57:20.053
and I knew the only
thing that separated us

57:20.140 --> 57:22.257
was a matter of a few years.

57:25.300 --> 57:26.654
What you got there, Uncle Gabe?

57:27.660 --> 57:29.094
I got me a ham sandwich.

57:29.180 --> 57:31.331
Rose gave me a ham sandwich.

57:33.820 --> 57:35.971
I lost touch with
everybody except Gabriel.

57:40.980 --> 57:41.970
But...

57:45.660 --> 57:47.492
I hope he's dead.

57:51.740 --> 57:54.414
I hope he found some peace.

57:54.500 --> 57:56.537
That's a heavy story, Pop.

57:57.940 --> 58:01.729
I didn't know you left
home when you was 14.

58:01.860 --> 58:03.897
Fourteen's kinda young
to be on your own.

58:03.980 --> 58:05.858
I don't know what I would've done.

58:06.620 --> 58:09.419
Well, I got up from that creek,
walked on down to Mobile.

58:09.500 --> 58:13.176
I was through with farming. I
figured I'd do better in the cities.

58:13.260 --> 58:15.092
So,
I walked the 200 miles to Mobile.

58:15.180 --> 58:18.776
Wait a minute,
you ain't walked no 200 miles, Pop.

58:18.860 --> 58:20.808
Ain't nobody gonna
walk no 200 miles.

58:20.878 --> 58:22.934
You talking about
some walking there!

58:23.020 --> 58:25.774
That's the only way you got
anywhere back in them days.

58:25.860 --> 58:28.694
Shit! Damn if I wouldn't have
hitched a ride with somebody.

58:28.780 --> 58:30.453
Who you gonna hitch it with?

58:30.540 --> 58:32.338
There ain't no cars and
things like they got now.

58:32.420 --> 58:34.059
We talking about 1918.

58:34.140 --> 58:35.699
What you all out here gettin' into?

58:35.780 --> 58:37.976
I'm telling Lyons
how good he got it.

58:38.060 --> 58:39.335
He don't know nothing
about this I'm talking.

58:39.420 --> 58:40.744
Lyons,
that was Bonnie on the phone.

58:40.814 --> 58:42.174
She says you supposed
to pick her up.

58:42.260 --> 58:44.013
Yeah, okay, Rose.

58:44.100 --> 58:46.820
I walked on down to Mobile,

58:46.900 --> 58:50.177
hitched up with some fellows
that was coming up this way.

58:50.260 --> 58:51.899
Got up here and found out,

58:51.980 --> 58:53.494
not only could you not get a job,

58:53.620 --> 58:55.134
you couldn't find no place to live.

58:55.220 --> 58:57.860
I thought I was in freedom.

58:58.140 --> 59:00.530
Colored folks living down
there on the riverbanks

59:00.620 --> 59:02.851
in whatever kind of shelter
they could find for themselves.

59:02.940 --> 59:05.409
Right down there under
the Brady Street Bridge.

59:05.820 --> 59:09.131
Living down there in shacks made
out of sticks and tar paper.

59:10.180 --> 59:11.899
Messed around down there.

59:11.980 --> 59:14.495
Went from bad to worse.
Started stealing.

59:14.580 --> 59:17.175
First, it was food.
Then I figure I steal me some money,

59:17.260 --> 59:19.729
I can buy me some food,
buy me some shoes, too.

59:20.060 --> 59:21.813
One thing led to another.
Met your mama.

59:22.260 --> 59:24.570
I was young, anxious to be a man.

59:25.140 --> 59:27.496
I met your mama and had you.
Why'd I do that for?

59:27.580 --> 59:30.015
Now, I got to worry about
feeding you and her.

59:30.100 --> 59:31.580
Got to steal three times as much.

59:32.420 --> 59:35.811
I went out one day looking
for somebody to rob.

59:35.940 --> 59:37.215
That's what I was, I was a robber.

59:37.940 --> 59:39.533
I'mma tell you the truth.

59:39.620 --> 59:41.532
I'm ashamed of it today,
but it's the truth.

59:42.580 --> 59:44.458
I went to rob this fella,
I pull out my knife.

59:44.540 --> 59:46.691
He pulled out a gun,
shot me in the chest.

59:46.780 --> 59:50.012
It felt like somebody had taken a
hot branding iron and laid it on me.

59:50.100 --> 59:53.138
Now, when he shot me,
I jumped at him with my knife,

59:55.020 --> 59:56.852
and they say I killed him.

59:56.940 --> 59:59.011
Locked me up, put me in the
penitentiary for 15 years.

59:59.100 --> 01:00:00.454
That's where I met Bono.

01:00:01.020 --> 01:00:03.296
Where I learned how
to play baseball.

01:00:03.380 --> 01:00:04.894
Got out that place,
and your mama had taken you,

01:00:04.980 --> 01:00:06.972
went on to make a life without me.

01:00:07.060 --> 01:00:09.131
Fifteen years was a long
time for her to wait.

01:00:09.220 --> 01:00:11.098
But that 15 years cured
me of that robbing stuff.

01:00:11.180 --> 01:00:12.534
Rose'll tell you.

01:00:12.620 --> 01:00:14.896
I first met her, she ask me if I had

01:00:14.980 --> 01:00:17.131
gotten all that foolishness
out of my system.

01:00:17.220 --> 01:00:19.052
I said, "Baby,
it's you and baseball,

01:00:19.140 --> 01:00:20.859
"all what count to me."
You hear me, Bono?

01:00:20.940 --> 01:00:23.580
And I meant it, too.
She said, "Which one come first?"

01:00:23.660 --> 01:00:26.732
I said, "Well,
ain't no doubt it's baseball.

01:00:26.820 --> 01:00:28.777
"But you stick and get old with me,

01:00:28.860 --> 01:00:30.419
"and we'll both
outlive this baseball."

01:00:30.500 --> 01:00:32.617
Am I right, Rose?

01:00:33.820 --> 01:00:34.890
And it's true.

01:00:34.980 --> 01:00:36.733
Man, hush your mouth.
You ain't say no such thing.

01:00:36.820 --> 01:00:37.623
Talkin' about, "Baby,

01:00:37.693 --> 01:00:39.415
you know you'll always
be number one with me."

01:00:39.500 --> 01:00:42.095
That's what you was talking.

01:00:42.180 --> 01:00:44.649
- That's why I love this woman.
- Rose will keep you straight.

01:00:44.740 --> 01:00:46.857
You get off the track,
she'll straighten you up.

01:00:46.940 --> 01:00:48.294
Lyons,
you better get on up and get Bonnie.

01:00:48.380 --> 01:00:49.860
She waiting on you.

01:00:49.940 --> 01:00:51.215
- Hey, Pop.
- Yeah?

01:00:51.300 --> 01:00:53.337
You ought to come down to the Grill,
hear me play.

01:00:53.980 --> 01:00:55.699
Man, I ain't goin' down there.

01:00:55.780 --> 01:00:57.214
I'm too old to be hanging
out in them clubs.

01:00:57.300 --> 01:01:00.577
You got to be good to
play down at the Grill.

01:01:00.660 --> 01:01:02.140
Come on, Pop.

01:01:02.220 --> 01:01:06.009
- I got to get up in the morning.
- Well, you ain't gotta stay long.

01:01:07.020 --> 01:01:10.696
No, I'm gonna eat my
supper and go to bed.

01:01:11.780 --> 01:01:14.614
Well, I got to go.
I'll see you later.

01:01:18.220 --> 01:01:20.416
Don't you come by my
house on my payday!

01:01:20.820 --> 01:01:22.891
And pick up the phone,
let somebody know you coming,

01:01:23.020 --> 01:01:24.977
and bring Bonnie,
you know I'm always glad to see her.

01:01:25.060 --> 01:01:28.531
I'll do that, Rose.
You take care now.

01:01:28.620 --> 01:01:30.134
- See you, Pop.
- All right.

01:01:30.220 --> 01:01:32.291
See you, Mr. Bono.

01:01:32.380 --> 01:01:35.418
- See you, Uncle Gabe!
- Lyons! King of the Jungle!

01:01:36.660 --> 01:01:37.855
Supper ready, woman?

01:01:37.940 --> 01:01:39.454
Me and you got some
business to take care of.

01:01:39.580 --> 01:01:41.856
- I'mma tear it up, too.
- Troy, I done told you now!

01:01:41.940 --> 01:01:44.177
Hell, woman, it's Bono.
Bono like family.

01:01:44.247 --> 01:01:46.093
I done know this nigger since...

01:01:46.180 --> 01:01:48.649
- How long have I known you?
- It's been a long time.

01:01:48.740 --> 01:01:51.130
I done known this nigger
since Skippy was a pup!

01:01:51.220 --> 01:01:53.052
Me and him done been
through some times!

01:01:53.140 --> 01:01:54.813
You sure are right about that.

01:01:54.900 --> 01:01:56.892
Hell, I known him longer
than I known you, Rose,

01:01:56.980 --> 01:01:58.812
and we still standin'
shoulder to shoulder.

01:01:58.900 --> 01:02:02.291
Look here, Bono, a man can't
ask for no more than that.

01:02:02.380 --> 01:02:03.609
I love you, nigger.

01:02:03.700 --> 01:02:05.657
Hell! I love you, too.

01:02:05.740 --> 01:02:08.733
But I got to get home, see my woman.
You got yours in hand.

01:02:09.140 --> 01:02:10.574
I got to go get mine.

01:02:12.540 --> 01:02:14.418
What you do that for, Pop?

01:02:14.500 --> 01:02:15.854
What's the matter?
Cory, what's the matter?

01:02:15.940 --> 01:02:17.693
Pop done went up to the
school and told Coach Zellman

01:02:17.780 --> 01:02:18.930
I can't play football no more.

01:02:19.020 --> 01:02:20.534
Wouldn't even let me play the game.

01:02:20.660 --> 01:02:22.140
Told him to tell the
recruiter not to come.

01:02:22.220 --> 01:02:24.018
- Troy.
- What you Troying me for?

01:02:24.100 --> 01:02:25.693
Yeah, I did it.
And the boy knows why I did it.

01:02:25.780 --> 01:02:27.658
Why you wanna do that to me?
That was the one chance I had!

01:02:27.740 --> 01:02:29.174
Ain't nothing wrong with
Cory playing football, Troy.

01:02:29.260 --> 01:02:30.410
The boy lied to me.

01:02:30.500 --> 01:02:33.015
I told the nigger,
"You want to play football,

01:02:33.100 --> 01:02:34.375
"you keep up with your chores

01:02:34.460 --> 01:02:36.975
"hold that job down at the A&P."
That was the conditions.

01:02:37.060 --> 01:02:38.540
I stopped down to
see Mr. Stawicki...

01:02:38.620 --> 01:02:41.340
I can't work after school
during the football season, Pop.

01:02:41.420 --> 01:02:43.571
I tried to tell you Mr. Stawicki
was holding my job for me.

01:02:43.660 --> 01:02:44.966
You don't never want
to listen to nobody,

01:02:45.036 --> 01:02:46.375
and then you wanna go
and do this to me?

01:02:46.460 --> 01:02:48.019
I ain't done nothin' to you.
You done it to yourself.

01:02:48.100 --> 01:02:49.693
Just 'cause you didn't get a chance!

01:02:49.780 --> 01:02:51.772
You're just scared I'm gonna
be better than you, that's all!

01:02:57.580 --> 01:02:58.809
- Come here.
- Troy.

01:02:59.500 --> 01:03:00.490
Troy.

01:03:07.500 --> 01:03:08.820
Pick it up.

01:03:17.820 --> 01:03:19.459
Put it on.

01:03:27.180 --> 01:03:29.058
Strap it up.

01:03:34.660 --> 01:03:36.014
All right.

01:03:37.580 --> 01:03:39.333
See, you done made a mistake.

01:03:39.500 --> 01:03:40.458
I didn't even do nothing!

01:03:40.528 --> 01:03:42.060
I'll tell you what
your mistake was.

01:03:42.860 --> 01:03:46.410
You swung at the ball
and you didn't hit it.

01:03:46.540 --> 01:03:50.170
That's strike one.
You in the batter's box now.

01:03:50.820 --> 01:03:53.380
You swung and you missed, see?

01:03:54.620 --> 01:03:55.849
That's strike one.

01:03:58.900 --> 01:04:01.813
Don't you strike out.

01:05:34.940 --> 01:05:37.774
Cory, why don't you come on in here,
help me clean out these cupboards.

01:05:37.940 --> 01:05:41.217
I ain't quitting the team.
I don't care what Papa says.

01:05:41.300 --> 01:05:43.451
I'll talk to him when he get back.

01:05:43.820 --> 01:05:45.220
He had to go see
about your Uncle Gabe.

01:05:45.300 --> 01:05:46.575
Police done arrested him again.

01:05:46.700 --> 01:05:48.373
Said he was disturbing the peace.

01:05:48.460 --> 01:05:49.814
He'll be back directly.

01:05:49.900 --> 01:05:52.460
Come on in here and help me
clean out these cupboards.

01:05:52.580 --> 01:05:53.809
Come on.

01:06:04.140 --> 01:06:06.018
Troy, what they say down there?

01:06:06.100 --> 01:06:09.411
They ain't said nothing.
I give them $50, they let him go.

01:06:09.500 --> 01:06:11.378
I'll talk to you about it.

01:06:11.460 --> 01:06:12.450
Where Cory?

01:06:12.540 --> 01:06:14.850
He in the house, helping me
clean out these cupboards.

01:06:14.980 --> 01:06:16.812
All right,
tell him to get his butt out here.

01:06:19.340 --> 01:06:21.297
All they want is the money.

01:06:21.380 --> 01:06:23.576
This makes six, seven times,
I done went down there and got him.

01:06:23.660 --> 01:06:25.891
See me coming,
they stick out their hands.

01:06:25.980 --> 01:06:28.734
Yeah, I know what you mean. That's
all they care about, that money.

01:06:28.820 --> 01:06:30.891
They don't care about what's right.

01:06:32.260 --> 01:06:36.732
Nigger, why you got to
go and get some hardwood?

01:06:36.820 --> 01:06:39.096
You ain't doing nothin'
but building a little old fence.

01:06:39.180 --> 01:06:41.092
Get you some soft pinewood.
That's all you need.

01:06:41.180 --> 01:06:42.773
I know what I'm doing.
This outside wood.

01:06:42.860 --> 01:06:45.091
You put pinewood inside the house.

01:06:45.180 --> 01:06:48.252
Pinewood inside wood.
This here the outside wood.

01:06:48.340 --> 01:06:50.536
Now tell me,
where the fence gonna be?

01:06:51.940 --> 01:06:53.738
You don't need this wood.

01:06:53.820 --> 01:06:55.300
You can put it up with pinewood,

01:06:55.380 --> 01:06:57.656
and it'll stand as long as you
gonna be here looking at it.

01:06:57.740 --> 01:06:59.220
How you know how long I'm
gonna be here, nigger?

01:06:59.300 --> 01:07:00.973
Hell, I might live forever.

01:07:01.060 --> 01:07:03.655
I'll live longer
than old man Horsely.

01:07:03.740 --> 01:07:05.459
That's what Magee used to say.

01:07:05.540 --> 01:07:06.288
Magee a damn fool.

01:07:06.358 --> 01:07:07.896
Now you tell me who
you ever heard of

01:07:07.980 --> 01:07:11.018
gonna pull their own teeth
with a pair of rusty pliers?

01:07:11.100 --> 01:07:12.216
They're old folks.

01:07:12.300 --> 01:07:14.212
My granddaddy used to pull
his teeth with pliers.

01:07:14.300 --> 01:07:16.417
They ain't had no dentists
for colored folk back then.

01:07:16.540 --> 01:07:19.055
Well, get clean pliers.
You understand? Clean pliers.

01:07:19.140 --> 01:07:21.700
Sterilize them.
Besides, we ain't living back then.

01:07:22.140 --> 01:07:24.939
All he had to do was go
down to Doc Goldblum's.

01:07:25.020 --> 01:07:27.580
I see where you and that
Tallahassee gal, that Alberta,

01:07:28.220 --> 01:07:30.177
see where you all done got tight.

01:07:30.260 --> 01:07:31.535
What you mean, "got tight"?

01:07:31.620 --> 01:07:33.657
I see where you be laughing and
joking with her all the time.

01:07:33.740 --> 01:07:36.460
I laugh and joke with 'em all.
Bono, you know me.

01:07:36.540 --> 01:07:38.532
Ain't the kind of laughing
and joking I'm talking about.

01:07:40.260 --> 01:07:41.660
How you doing, Mr. Bono?

01:07:41.740 --> 01:07:43.459
Cory, get that saw from
Bono and cut some wood.

01:07:43.540 --> 01:07:45.975
He talking about
wood too hard to cut.

01:07:46.060 --> 01:07:47.653
Stand back there, Jim.

01:07:47.780 --> 01:07:49.009
Let the young boy show
you how it's done.

01:07:49.100 --> 01:07:51.251
He's sure welcome to it.

01:07:55.660 --> 01:07:59.893
Look at that. Big, ol' strong boy,
looks like Joe Louis.

01:08:01.100 --> 01:08:02.580
Hell, I must be getting old

01:08:02.660 --> 01:08:04.617
the way I'm watching that
boy whip through that wood.

01:08:04.820 --> 01:08:07.210
I don't see why Mama wants a
fence around no yard no way.

01:08:07.340 --> 01:08:08.376
Damn if I know, either.

01:08:08.460 --> 01:08:10.531
I don't know what the hell
she keeping out with it.

01:08:10.620 --> 01:08:12.612
She ain't got nothing nobody wants.

01:08:13.860 --> 01:08:15.738
Some people build fences
to keep people out,

01:08:15.820 --> 01:08:18.130
and other people build
fences to keep people in.

01:08:19.100 --> 01:08:21.410
Rose wants to hold on to you all.
She loves you.

01:08:22.140 --> 01:08:25.133
Hell, nigger, I don't need nobody
to tell me my wife loves me.

01:08:25.220 --> 01:08:28.691
Cory, go in the house and see
if you can find the other saw.

01:08:28.819 --> 01:08:30.459
Where's it at?

01:08:30.540 --> 01:08:33.339
I said find it.
Look for it till you find it.

01:08:36.140 --> 01:08:39.531
What is that supposed to mean?
Want to keep us in?

01:08:54.100 --> 01:08:55.216
Troy,

01:08:56.020 --> 01:08:59.569
I done known you seem like
damn near my whole life.

01:08:59.660 --> 01:09:02.413
You and Rose both. I known both
of you all for a long time.

01:09:03.500 --> 01:09:05.969
I remember when you met Rose.

01:09:06.060 --> 01:09:09.019
When you was hitting them
baseball out of the park.

01:09:09.380 --> 01:09:11.611
A lot of them old gals
was after you then.

01:09:11.740 --> 01:09:13.697
You had the pick of the litter.

01:09:13.779 --> 01:09:17.376
When you picked Rose,
I was happy for you.

01:09:18.260 --> 01:09:21.651
That's the first time I
knew you had any sense.

01:09:22.020 --> 01:09:24.933
I said,
"My man Troy knows what he's doing.

01:09:25.020 --> 01:09:28.171
"I'm gonna follow this nigger,
he might take me somewhere."

01:09:28.580 --> 01:09:30.617
I been following you, too.

01:09:30.700 --> 01:09:34.250
I done learned a whole heap of
things about life watching you.

01:09:35.740 --> 01:09:38.971
I done learned how to
tell where the shit lies.

01:09:39.100 --> 01:09:41.376
How to tell it from the alfalfa.

01:09:42.100 --> 01:09:44.569
You done learned me a lot of things.

01:09:44.660 --> 01:09:47.255
Showed me how to not
make the same mistakes.

01:09:47.740 --> 01:09:49.537
To take life as it come along,

01:09:49.620 --> 01:09:52.294
keep putting one foot
in front of the other.

01:09:52.779 --> 01:09:55.420
- Rose is a good woman, Troy.
- I know she a good woman.

01:09:55.500 --> 01:09:57.014
I've been married
to her for 18 years.

01:09:57.100 --> 01:09:58.454
What you got on your mind, Bono?

01:09:58.540 --> 01:10:00.930
I just say she's a good woman,
like I say anything.

01:10:01.020 --> 01:10:02.340
I ain't got to have
nothing on my mind.

01:10:02.420 --> 01:10:03.414
You just say she a good woman

01:10:03.484 --> 01:10:04.856
and leave it hanging
out there like that?

01:10:04.940 --> 01:10:06.010
Why are you telling
me she a good woman?

01:10:06.100 --> 01:10:08.934
She loves you, Troy. Rose loves you.

01:10:09.020 --> 01:10:10.215
You saying I don't measure up?

01:10:10.340 --> 01:10:11.569
That's what you tryin' to say.

01:10:11.660 --> 01:10:13.379
I don't measure up
'cause I'm seeing this other gal.

01:10:13.460 --> 01:10:14.610
I know what you tryin' to say.

01:10:14.700 --> 01:10:16.851
I know what Rose means to you, Troy.

01:10:16.940 --> 01:10:19.899
I'm just tryin' to say I
don't want to see you mess up.

01:10:21.900 --> 01:10:23.095
Yeah.

01:10:26.780 --> 01:10:29.454
Well, I appreciate that, Bono.

01:10:31.500 --> 01:10:33.328
If you was messing
around on Lucille,

01:10:33.398 --> 01:10:35.176
I'd be telling you the same thing.

01:10:35.260 --> 01:10:36.774
That's all I got to say.

01:10:37.820 --> 01:10:40.779
I just say that
'cause I love you both.

01:10:42.140 --> 01:10:43.813
Yeah.

01:10:44.660 --> 01:10:47.129
You know me. I wasn't out
there looking for nothing.

01:10:47.220 --> 01:10:49.655
You can't find a better
woman than Rose, I know that.

01:10:49.980 --> 01:10:52.814
But it seems like this
woman just stuck on to me

01:10:52.900 --> 01:10:54.050
where I can't shake her loose.

01:10:54.140 --> 01:10:56.668
I done wrestled with it and
tried to throw her off,

01:10:56.738 --> 01:10:58.255
but now she stuck on tighter.

01:10:58.340 --> 01:11:00.650
And now she stuck on for good.

01:11:00.740 --> 01:11:01.585
You's in control.

01:11:01.655 --> 01:11:03.494
That's what you tell
me all the time.

01:11:03.580 --> 01:11:05.333
You responsible for what you do.

01:11:05.420 --> 01:11:07.173
I ain't ducking the
responsibility of it.

01:11:07.260 --> 01:11:09.650
As long as it set right in my heart,
then I'm okay.

01:11:09.740 --> 01:11:12.653
'Cause that's all I listen to. It
tell me right and wrong every time.

01:11:12.740 --> 01:11:14.572
And I ain't talking about
doing Rose no bad turn.

01:11:14.660 --> 01:11:16.094
I love Rose.

01:11:16.180 --> 01:11:17.739
She done carried me a long ways,

01:11:17.820 --> 01:11:19.174
and I love and respect her for that.

01:11:19.260 --> 01:11:20.410
I know you do.

01:11:20.500 --> 01:11:22.617
That's why I don't want
to see you hurt her.

01:11:22.700 --> 01:11:25.090
But what you gonna do
when she finds out?

01:11:25.540 --> 01:11:27.611
What you got then?

01:11:27.700 --> 01:11:29.100
You try to juggle both of them,

01:11:29.180 --> 01:11:30.933
sooner or later,
you gonna drop one of them.

01:11:31.020 --> 01:11:33.216
- That's common sense.
- I know what you're saying, Bono.

01:11:34.940 --> 01:11:36.977
I been trying to figure
a way to work it out.

01:11:37.060 --> 01:11:39.097
Work it out right, Troy.

01:11:39.220 --> 01:11:41.860
I ain't trying to get all up
between you and Rose's business,

01:11:41.940 --> 01:11:44.136
but work it, so it come out right.

01:11:44.220 --> 01:11:46.451
Hell, I get all between
you and Lucille's business.

01:11:46.540 --> 01:11:48.054
And when you gonna buy that woman

01:11:48.140 --> 01:11:49.494
that refrigerator she be wanting?

01:11:49.580 --> 01:11:51.253
And don't tell me you
ain't got no money.

01:11:51.340 --> 01:11:52.615
I know who your banker is.

01:11:52.700 --> 01:11:55.215
Mellon don't need that money as bad
as Lucille wants that refrigerator.

01:11:55.300 --> 01:11:56.290
I know that.

01:11:56.380 --> 01:11:57.496
- Tell you what I'll do.
- What?

01:11:57.580 --> 01:11:59.572
When you finish building
this fence for Rose,

01:11:59.660 --> 01:12:01.299
I'll buy Lucille that refrigerator.

01:12:01.380 --> 01:12:04.259
You done stuck your
foot in your mouth now.

01:12:05.380 --> 01:12:06.973
Hey, nigger, where you going?

01:12:07.060 --> 01:12:08.289
I'm going home.

01:12:08.380 --> 01:12:10.212
I know you don't expect
me to help you now.

01:12:10.300 --> 01:12:11.734
I'm protecting my money.

01:12:12.220 --> 01:12:15.133
I want to see you put
that fence up by yourself.

01:12:15.220 --> 01:12:16.813
That's what I want to see.

01:12:16.900 --> 01:12:19.131
You'll be here another
six months without me.

01:12:19.260 --> 01:12:20.580
Nigger, you ain't right.

01:12:20.660 --> 01:12:22.333
When it come to my money,

01:12:22.420 --> 01:12:25.492
I'm right as fireworks
on the Fourth of July.

01:12:25.580 --> 01:12:28.732
We gonna see.
You better get out your bank book!

01:13:20.780 --> 01:13:22.851
What they say down there?
What's happening with Gabe?

01:13:22.940 --> 01:13:25.899
I went down there and got him out.
Cost me $50.

01:13:25.980 --> 01:13:27.414
Said he was disturbing the peace.

01:13:27.500 --> 01:13:29.935
Judge set up a hearing
for him in three weeks

01:13:30.020 --> 01:13:32.615
to show cause why he
shouldn't be recommitted.

01:13:32.700 --> 01:13:34.373
What'd you say?
What'd you tell the judge?

01:13:34.780 --> 01:13:36.419
I told him I'd take care of him.

01:13:36.500 --> 01:13:38.059
It didn't make no sense
to recommit the man.

01:13:38.140 --> 01:13:39.540
He stuck out his big greasy palm,

01:13:39.620 --> 01:13:42.294
told me to give him $50
and take him on home.

01:13:42.380 --> 01:13:44.292
Where's he at now?
Where'd he go off to?

01:13:44.380 --> 01:13:46.292
Gone about his business. He don't
need nobody to hold his hand.

01:13:46.380 --> 01:13:48.576
Well, I don't know, seem like that
would be the best place for him.

01:13:48.660 --> 01:13:49.650
To put him in a hospital.

01:13:49.740 --> 01:13:52.340
I know what you gonna say, but
that's what I think would be best.

01:13:52.420 --> 01:13:54.059
Man had his life ruined
fighting for what?

01:13:54.140 --> 01:13:55.369
Now, they want to take
him and lock him up?

01:13:55.460 --> 01:13:57.770
Let him be free.
Man ain't bothering nobody.

01:13:58.780 --> 01:14:01.693
Everybody got their own way
of looking at it, I guess.

01:14:01.820 --> 01:14:03.049
Come on, get your lunch.

01:14:03.140 --> 01:14:04.733
I got some lima beans and
cornbread in the oven.

01:14:04.820 --> 01:14:05.890
Come on, get somethin' to eat.

01:14:05.980 --> 01:14:07.573
Ain't no sense in you
fretting over Gabe.

01:14:07.700 --> 01:14:08.895
Rose, I got something to tell you.

01:14:09.020 --> 01:14:11.107
Wait till I put the
food on the table.

01:14:11.177 --> 01:14:11.854
Rose...

01:14:12.700 --> 01:14:15.534
Now,
I don't know how to tell you this.

01:14:19.460 --> 01:14:21.497
And I can't explain it none.

01:14:21.580 --> 01:14:24.732
It just sort of grows on you.

01:14:25.740 --> 01:14:27.783
It started off like a little bush,

01:14:27.853 --> 01:14:30.257
next thing you know,
it's a whole forest.

01:14:30.340 --> 01:14:33.538
- Troy, what is you talking about?
- I'm talking, woman. Let me talk.

01:14:33.620 --> 01:14:35.418
I'm trying to tell you,

01:14:35.500 --> 01:14:37.935
find a way to tell you that

01:14:43.020 --> 01:14:45.330
I'm gonna be a daddy.

01:14:47.500 --> 01:14:49.776
Yeah, I'm gonna be somebody's daddy.

01:14:54.340 --> 01:14:57.094
Troy, you ain't telling me this.
You're gonna be what?

01:14:57.180 --> 01:14:58.500
- You're gonna be somebody's daddy?
- Rose...

01:14:58.580 --> 01:14:59.650
You're telling your wife this?

01:14:59.740 --> 01:15:00.776
Now...

01:15:00.860 --> 01:15:03.091
Hey, Troy! Hey, Rose!

01:15:03.180 --> 01:15:05.775
I got to wait 18 years to
hear something like this?

01:15:05.860 --> 01:15:07.089
Hey, Rose.

01:15:09.020 --> 01:15:11.376
I got a flower for you.

01:15:14.060 --> 01:15:17.610
That's a rose.
The same rose like you is.

01:15:22.620 --> 01:15:24.054
Thanks, Gabe.

01:15:24.140 --> 01:15:25.540
Troy, you ain't mad at me?

01:15:25.620 --> 01:15:27.054
Them bad mens come and put me away.

01:15:27.140 --> 01:15:29.530
- You ain't mad at me?
- No. No, I ain't mad at you.

01:15:29.620 --> 01:15:31.532
Eighteen years,
and you want to come with this?

01:15:31.660 --> 01:15:34.300
See what I got?
Got a brand-new quarter.

01:15:37.220 --> 01:15:38.290
Rose, it's just that...

01:15:38.380 --> 01:15:40.576
Ain't nothing you can say, Troy.
Ain't no explaining it.

01:15:40.660 --> 01:15:43.300
The fella that give me this
quarter had a whole mess of 'em!

01:15:43.420 --> 01:15:45.889
I'm gonna keep this quarter
till it stops shining.

01:15:45.980 --> 01:15:48.540
Gabe, go on up front now. I got
some watermelon in the Frigidaire.

01:15:48.620 --> 01:15:49.770
Go on. I'll get you a piece.

01:15:49.860 --> 01:15:52.580
Say, Rose, you know,
I was chasing hellhounds,

01:15:52.660 --> 01:15:55.573
and them bad mens come and
get me and take me away.

01:15:55.660 --> 01:15:57.652
Troy helped me.
He come down there and told them

01:15:57.740 --> 01:16:00.653
they better let me go
before he beat them up!

01:16:00.740 --> 01:16:02.015
Yeah, he did!

01:16:02.100 --> 01:16:04.376
Go up front now, Gabe.
I'll get you some watermelon.

01:16:04.460 --> 01:16:05.940
Them bad men is gone now.

01:16:06.020 --> 01:16:08.376
Okay.
Rose gonna give me some watermelon,

01:16:08.460 --> 01:16:10.929
the kind with the stripes on it.

01:16:16.420 --> 01:16:17.854
Why, Troy?

01:16:19.620 --> 01:16:20.849
Why?

01:16:20.940 --> 01:16:26.379
After all these years,
you come dragging this in to me now?

01:16:26.460 --> 01:16:28.611
It don't make no sense at your age.

01:16:29.300 --> 01:16:33.089
I could've expected this 10,
or 15 years ago, but not now.

01:16:33.380 --> 01:16:35.611
Age ain't got nothing to do with it,
Rose.

01:16:39.700 --> 01:16:42.977
I done tried to be
everything a wife should be.

01:16:44.980 --> 01:16:46.255
Everything a wife could be.

01:16:46.340 --> 01:16:47.615
I've been married 18 years,

01:16:47.700 --> 01:16:50.215
and now, I got to live to
see the day you tell me

01:16:50.300 --> 01:16:53.816
you been seeing another woman
and done fathered a child by her.

01:17:06.980 --> 01:17:10.974
And you know I never wanted
no half-nothing in my family!

01:17:13.980 --> 01:17:15.255
My whole family is half.

01:17:15.340 --> 01:17:17.172
Everybody got different
fathers and mothers

01:17:17.260 --> 01:17:18.740
and my two sisters and my brothers.

01:17:18.820 --> 01:17:20.413
You could hardly tell who's who.

01:17:20.500 --> 01:17:22.253
Could never sit down and
talk about Papa and Mama.

01:17:22.340 --> 01:17:24.980
It was always your papa,
your mama, my papa, my mama.

01:17:25.060 --> 01:17:27.575
And I ain't never wanted
that for none of my children!

01:17:27.660 --> 01:17:28.804
And now, you want
to drag your behind

01:17:28.874 --> 01:17:30.176
in here and tell me
something like this!

01:17:30.260 --> 01:17:32.217
Stop it now. You ought to know.
It's time for you to know.

01:17:32.300 --> 01:17:34.019
Well, I don't want to know,
God damn it!

01:17:54.020 --> 01:17:55.090
Rose?

01:17:58.220 --> 01:18:01.611
I just can't make it go away.
It's done now.

01:18:01.700 --> 01:18:05.614
I can't wish the circumstances
of the thing away.

01:18:05.780 --> 01:18:08.375
And you don't want to, either.

01:18:08.460 --> 01:18:10.258
Maybe you want to wish
me and my boy away.

01:18:10.340 --> 01:18:11.694
Maybe that's what you want.

01:18:11.820 --> 01:18:14.289
Well, you can't wish us away.

01:18:14.380 --> 01:18:16.337
I got 18 years of my
life invested in you.

01:18:16.420 --> 01:18:18.457
You ought to have stayed upstairs
in my bed where you belong.

01:18:18.540 --> 01:18:21.135
Now, listen to me.
We can get a handle on this thing.

01:18:21.220 --> 01:18:23.052
We can talk this out,
come to an understanding.

01:18:23.140 --> 01:18:24.369
All of a sudden it's "we."

01:18:24.500 --> 01:18:25.729
Where was "we"
at when you were down there,

01:18:25.820 --> 01:18:27.140
rolling around with
some godforsaken woman?

01:18:27.220 --> 01:18:28.400
"We"
should've come to an understanding

01:18:28.470 --> 01:18:30.054
before you started making
a damn fool of yourself!

01:18:30.140 --> 01:18:31.434
You're a day late
and a dollar short

01:18:31.504 --> 01:18:33.014
when it comes to an
understanding with me.

01:18:33.100 --> 01:18:38.858
Rose, it's just that she
gives me a different idea.

01:18:39.380 --> 01:18:42.532
A different understanding
about myself.

01:18:42.620 --> 01:18:46.091
I can step out of this house
and get away from the pressures

01:18:46.180 --> 01:18:47.534
and the problems,
be a different man.

01:18:47.620 --> 01:18:49.418
I ain't got to worry about
how I'll get the roof fixed,

01:18:49.500 --> 01:18:51.139
or pay the bills, or...

01:18:51.220 --> 01:18:52.540
I can just

01:18:54.500 --> 01:18:57.095
be a part of myself I
ain't never been before.

01:18:58.300 --> 01:19:00.451
What I want to know is...

01:19:02.980 --> 01:19:05.449
What I want to know

01:19:05.580 --> 01:19:08.220
is do you plan to
continue seeing her?

01:19:08.300 --> 01:19:10.610
That's all you can say to me.

01:19:11.900 --> 01:19:14.047
I could sit up in
her house and laugh.

01:19:14.117 --> 01:19:15.974
You understand what I'm saying?

01:19:16.060 --> 01:19:18.655
I could laugh out loud,
and it feels good.

01:19:18.740 --> 01:19:20.971
It reaches all the way down
to the bottom of my shoes.

01:19:21.060 --> 01:19:22.255
Rose, I...

01:19:24.660 --> 01:19:27.459
I can't give that up.

01:19:33.260 --> 01:19:35.411
Well, maybe you ought to go on
and stay down there with her,

01:19:35.500 --> 01:19:37.173
if she's a better woman than me.

01:19:37.260 --> 01:19:39.013
It ain't about nobody being
a better woman, or nothing.

01:19:39.100 --> 01:19:40.420
Rose, you ain't to blame.

01:19:40.500 --> 01:19:42.776
A man couldn't ask for a
better wife than you've been.

01:19:42.860 --> 01:19:44.340
I'm responsible for it.

01:19:44.420 --> 01:19:45.979
I done locked myself into a pattern,

01:19:46.060 --> 01:19:48.052
trying to take care of you all,
that I forgot about myself.

01:19:48.140 --> 01:19:49.779
Well, what the hell was I there for?

01:19:49.860 --> 01:19:51.419
That was my job,
not somebody else's.

01:19:51.500 --> 01:19:54.618
Rose, listen to me. I done tried
all my life to live decent.

01:19:54.700 --> 01:19:57.613
To live a clean, hard, useful life.

01:19:57.700 --> 01:20:00.852
I try to be a good husband to you,
in every way I know how.

01:20:00.940 --> 01:20:03.136
Maybe I come into the world
backwards, I don't know,

01:20:03.220 --> 01:20:06.531
but you're born with two strikes on
you before you come to the plate.

01:20:06.620 --> 01:20:07.736
You got to guard it closely,

01:20:07.820 --> 01:20:10.460
always looking for the
curveball on the inside corner.

01:20:10.540 --> 01:20:12.179
You can't afford a called strike.

01:20:12.260 --> 01:20:13.614
You can't let nothing get past you.

01:20:13.700 --> 01:20:15.817
If you're going down,
you're doing down swinging.

01:20:15.900 --> 01:20:18.620
Everything lined up against you!

01:20:20.300 --> 01:20:21.814
What you gonna do?

01:20:23.420 --> 01:20:25.855
I fooled them, Rose. I bunted.

01:20:26.300 --> 01:20:30.135
When I found you and Cory and a
halfway decent job, I was safe.

01:20:30.220 --> 01:20:32.416
Couldn't nothing touch me!

01:20:32.500 --> 01:20:33.934
I wasn't gonna strike out no more.

01:20:34.020 --> 01:20:35.420
I wasn't going back
to the penitentiary.

01:20:35.500 --> 01:20:37.856
I wasn't gonna lie in the
street with a bottle of wine.

01:20:37.940 --> 01:20:42.219
I was safe.
I had me a family, a job.

01:20:43.420 --> 01:20:46.094
I wasn't gonna get that last strike.

01:20:47.860 --> 01:20:50.739
I was standing on first base,

01:20:50.820 --> 01:20:52.777
waiting for one of them boys to
knock me in, to bring me home.

01:20:52.860 --> 01:20:54.658
You should have stayed in my bed,
Troy.

01:20:54.740 --> 01:20:56.174
Then I saw the gal,
she firmed up my backbone.

01:20:56.260 --> 01:20:59.219
I got to thinkin' that if I tried,
maybe I could steal second.

01:20:59.300 --> 01:21:00.780
- You understand?
- You should've held me tight.

01:21:00.860 --> 01:21:02.433
You should've grabbed
me and held on.

01:21:02.503 --> 01:21:04.251
I stood on first
base for 18 years,

01:21:04.340 --> 01:21:06.730
and I thought, well,
God damn it, go on for it!

01:21:06.820 --> 01:21:09.210
We ain't talking about baseball!

01:21:09.300 --> 01:21:11.610
We talking about you going off
and laying up with another woman,

01:21:11.700 --> 01:21:12.690
then bringing it home to me.

01:21:12.780 --> 01:21:15.056
That's what we're talking about.
We're not talkin' about no baseball!

01:21:15.140 --> 01:21:16.290
Rose, you're not listening to me.

01:21:16.420 --> 01:21:19.299
I'm trying to explain it to
you the best way I know how.

01:21:20.860 --> 01:21:22.663
It's not easy for me to admit that

01:21:22.733 --> 01:21:25.332
I've been standing in the
same place for 18 years!

01:21:25.420 --> 01:21:27.935
Well, I've been standing with you!

01:21:28.020 --> 01:21:32.060
I've been right here with you, Troy!
I got a life, too.

01:21:32.140 --> 01:21:36.373
I gave 18 years of my life to
stand in the same spot as you!

01:21:36.460 --> 01:21:38.417
Don't you think I ever
wanted other things?

01:21:38.500 --> 01:21:40.617
Don't you think I
had dreams and hopes?

01:21:40.700 --> 01:21:43.295
What about my life? What about me?

01:21:43.380 --> 01:21:45.970
Don't you think it ever crossed
my mind to want to know other men?

01:21:46.060 --> 01:21:48.060
That I wanted to lay up somewhere

01:21:48.130 --> 01:21:50.373
and forget about my
responsibilities?

01:21:50.460 --> 01:21:52.053
That I wanted someone
to make me laugh,

01:21:52.140 --> 01:21:54.177
so I could feel good?

01:21:54.260 --> 01:21:56.331
You're not the only one
who's got wants and needs.

01:21:56.460 --> 01:21:58.372
But I held on to you, Troy.

01:21:58.460 --> 01:22:02.613
I took all my feelings,
my wants and needs and dreams,

01:22:02.700 --> 01:22:04.498
and I buried them inside you.

01:22:04.580 --> 01:22:06.856
I planted a seed and
watched and prayed over it.

01:22:06.940 --> 01:22:09.933
I planted myself inside
you and waited to bloom!

01:22:10.020 --> 01:22:13.855
And it didn't take me no 18 years to
realize the soil was hard and rocky,

01:22:13.940 --> 01:22:16.057
and it wasn't never gonna bloom!

01:22:16.140 --> 01:22:19.053
But I held on to you, Troy.
I held you tighter.

01:22:19.140 --> 01:22:21.132
You was my husband.

01:22:21.220 --> 01:22:23.860
I owed you everything I had.

01:22:23.940 --> 01:22:26.614
Every part of me I
could find to give you.

01:22:26.740 --> 01:22:30.529
And upstairs in that bedroom,
with the darkness falling in on me,

01:22:30.660 --> 01:22:34.734
I gave everything I had
to try and erase the doubt

01:22:34.820 --> 01:22:37.494
that you wasn't the
finest man in the world.

01:22:37.580 --> 01:22:40.254
And wherever you was going,
I was gonna be there with you,

01:22:40.380 --> 01:22:42.815
because you was my husband.

01:22:44.260 --> 01:22:47.253
'Cause that's the only way I
was gonna survive as your wife.

01:22:48.500 --> 01:22:50.406
You always talking
about what you give

01:22:50.476 --> 01:22:52.176
and what you don't have to give.

01:22:52.860 --> 01:22:54.579
But you take, too, Troy.

01:22:54.660 --> 01:22:57.300
You take and don't even
know nobody's giving.

01:22:57.380 --> 01:22:58.370
You say I take and don't give.

01:22:58.460 --> 01:22:59.610
Troy, you're hurting me.

01:22:59.700 --> 01:23:00.648
Troy, you're hurting my arm,
let go!

01:23:00.718 --> 01:23:01.612
I gave you everything I got.

01:23:01.700 --> 01:23:02.975
Don't you tell that lie on me.

01:23:03.060 --> 01:23:04.460
- Mama!
- Don't you tell that lie!

01:23:04.540 --> 01:23:06.054
Troy, you're hurting me!

01:23:06.660 --> 01:23:08.014
Troy! Troy!

01:23:08.420 --> 01:23:12.096
All right. That's strike two.

01:23:12.940 --> 01:23:17.139
You stay away from around me, boy.
Don't you strike out.

01:23:18.820 --> 01:23:20.812
You're living with a full count.

01:23:24.380 --> 01:23:26.178
Don't you strike out!

01:26:46.660 --> 01:26:48.492
Troy, I want to talk to you.

01:26:51.140 --> 01:26:53.211
All of a sudden?

01:26:55.260 --> 01:26:57.729
After all this time,
you want to talk to me, huh?

01:26:58.820 --> 01:27:00.300
You ain't wanted to
talk to me in months.

01:27:00.380 --> 01:27:01.700
You ain't wanted to
talk to me last night.

01:27:01.780 --> 01:27:03.260
You didn't want no parts of me then.

01:27:03.900 --> 01:27:05.892
What you want to
talk to me about now?

01:27:09.540 --> 01:27:12.499
- Tomorrow's Friday.
- I know what day tomorrow is.

01:27:12.580 --> 01:27:13.730
You think I don't know
tomorrow's Friday?

01:27:13.860 --> 01:27:16.011
My whole life, I ain't done nothing
but look to see Friday coming,

01:27:16.100 --> 01:27:17.420
and you got to tell me it's Friday.

01:27:17.500 --> 01:27:19.014
I want to know if
you're coming home.

01:27:19.580 --> 01:27:22.015
I always come home, Rose.
You know that.

01:27:22.100 --> 01:27:23.454
Ain't never been a
night I ain't come home.

01:27:23.580 --> 01:27:25.219
That ain't what I mean,
and you know it.

01:27:25.420 --> 01:27:28.857
I wanna know if you're coming
straight home after work.

01:27:28.940 --> 01:27:31.899
I figured I'd cash my check,
hang out at Taylors' with the boys.

01:27:31.980 --> 01:27:33.096
Maybe play a game of checkers.

01:27:33.180 --> 01:27:35.775
Troy, I can't live like this.
I won't live like this.

01:27:35.860 --> 01:27:37.260
You're living on
borrowed time with me.

01:27:37.340 --> 01:27:39.332
Been going on six months now,
you ain't been coming home.

01:27:39.420 --> 01:27:41.457
I come home every night.
Every night of the year.

01:27:41.540 --> 01:27:44.009
That's 365 days.

01:27:45.540 --> 01:27:48.135
I want you to come home
tomorrow after work.

01:27:53.140 --> 01:27:56.816
Rose, I don't mess up my pay.
You know that.

01:27:56.900 --> 01:27:58.778
I take my pay, I give it to you.

01:27:58.860 --> 01:28:02.217
I don't have no money but
what you give me back.

01:28:02.300 --> 01:28:05.452
I just want a little time to myself.

01:28:05.580 --> 01:28:06.730
A little time to enjoy life.

01:28:06.820 --> 01:28:08.698
What about me?
When's my time to enjoy life?

01:28:08.780 --> 01:28:10.851
I don't know what to tell you, Rose.
I'm doing the best I can.

01:28:10.940 --> 01:28:11.976
You ain't been comin'
home from work,

01:28:12.060 --> 01:28:13.414
but time enough to change
your clothes and run out.

01:28:13.500 --> 01:28:15.492
You wanna call that
the best you can do?

01:28:17.060 --> 01:28:20.132
I'm going over to the
hospital to see Alberta.

01:28:21.260 --> 01:28:22.933
She went into the
hospital this afternoon.

01:28:23.020 --> 01:28:26.457
Looks like she might
have the baby early.

01:28:27.340 --> 01:28:29.013
I won't be gone long.

01:28:35.420 --> 01:28:36.406
Well, you ought to know.

01:28:36.476 --> 01:28:38.489
They went over to Miss
Pearl's and got Gabe today.

01:28:38.580 --> 01:28:42.335
She said you told them to
go ahead and lock him up.

01:28:42.420 --> 01:28:46.380
I ain't said no such thing. Whoever
told you that is telling a lie.

01:28:46.460 --> 01:28:48.179
Miss Pearl ain't doing nothing
but telling a big, fat lie.

01:28:48.260 --> 01:28:50.138
She ain't had to tell me.
I read it on the papers.

01:28:50.220 --> 01:28:52.337
- What'd it say, huh?
- It said you told them to take him.

01:28:52.460 --> 01:28:54.611
Then they screwed that up,
just like they screw up everything.

01:28:54.700 --> 01:28:55.929
I ain't worried about what
they got on that paper.

01:28:56.020 --> 01:28:57.932
It say the government sends part
of the check to the hospital,

01:28:58.020 --> 01:28:59.090
the other part to you.

01:28:59.180 --> 01:29:00.819
I got nothing to do with that,
if that's the way it works.

01:29:00.900 --> 01:29:02.016
I don't make up the rules...

01:29:02.100 --> 01:29:03.375
You did Gabe just like you did Cory.

01:29:03.460 --> 01:29:04.655
You wouldn't sign
the paper for Cory,

01:29:04.740 --> 01:29:06.379
but you signed for Gabe!
You signed that paper!

01:29:06.460 --> 01:29:08.292
I told you I ain't signed nothing,
woman.

01:29:08.380 --> 01:29:09.939
Hell, the only thing I
signed was the release form.

01:29:10.060 --> 01:29:11.050
Hell, I can't read,

01:29:11.140 --> 01:29:12.460
I don't know what they
had on that paper.

01:29:12.540 --> 01:29:14.372
I ain't signed nothing
about sending Gabe away.

01:29:14.460 --> 01:29:16.611
I said send him to the hospital,
you said let him go free.

01:29:16.700 --> 01:29:17.690
Then you went down there

01:29:17.820 --> 01:29:19.254
and you signed him to the
hospital for half his money.

01:29:19.340 --> 01:29:20.363
You went back on yourself, Troy.

01:29:20.433 --> 01:29:21.616
You're gonna have
to answer for that.

01:29:21.740 --> 01:29:23.299
You just been over there
talking to Miss Pearl.

01:29:23.380 --> 01:29:24.608
She just mad 'cause
she ain't gettin'

01:29:24.678 --> 01:29:25.940
Gabe's rent money, that's all it is.

01:29:26.020 --> 01:29:27.454
Troy,
I seen where you signed the paper!

01:29:27.540 --> 01:29:28.656
You ain't seen nothing I signed!

01:29:28.740 --> 01:29:31.414
And what she doing got papers
on my brother for, anyway?

01:29:32.900 --> 01:29:35.176
Miss Pearl ain't doing nothing
but telling a big, fat lie,

01:29:35.260 --> 01:29:37.092
and I'm gonna tell her about it,
too!

01:29:43.060 --> 01:29:45.575
You ain't seen nothing I signed!

01:29:46.260 --> 01:29:47.660
Say...

01:29:49.540 --> 01:29:51.691
You ain't seen nothing I signed!

01:31:48.460 --> 01:31:49.860
Troy.

01:31:52.180 --> 01:31:53.694
Troy.

01:31:58.980 --> 01:32:01.779
That was the hospital.
Alberta had the baby.

01:32:03.220 --> 01:32:05.815
Yeah? What she have? What is it?

01:32:06.900 --> 01:32:08.380
It's a girl.

01:32:11.220 --> 01:32:12.779
I...

01:32:15.820 --> 01:32:18.051
I better get on down
there to see her.

01:32:19.900 --> 01:32:20.890
Troy.

01:32:21.060 --> 01:32:23.894
I got to go see her now, Rose.
That's only right.

01:32:29.140 --> 01:32:32.497
What's the matter?
Baby all right, ain't it?

01:32:35.740 --> 01:32:38.778
Alberta died having the baby.

01:32:40.020 --> 01:32:42.012
She died? You say she's dead?

01:32:45.180 --> 01:32:46.500
Alberta dead?

01:32:47.260 --> 01:32:49.650
They said they done all they could.
They...

01:32:51.100 --> 01:32:52.534
They couldn't do nothing for her.

01:33:24.380 --> 01:33:26.531
What about the baby? Baby all right?

01:33:28.460 --> 01:33:30.531
They say it's healthy.

01:33:32.860 --> 01:33:34.294
I wonder who's gonna bury her.

01:33:34.380 --> 01:33:35.416
She had a family, Rose.

01:33:35.500 --> 01:33:36.980
She wasn't living in
the world by herself.

01:33:37.060 --> 01:33:39.336
I know she wasn't living
in the world by herself.

01:33:39.420 --> 01:33:40.820
Next thing you wanna know
if she had any insurance.

01:33:40.900 --> 01:33:42.220
You ain't got to
talk to me like that!

01:33:42.300 --> 01:33:44.371
First thing that jumped out your
mouth. "Who's gonna bury her?"

01:33:44.500 --> 01:33:46.059
Like I'm finna take
that task on for myself.

01:33:46.140 --> 01:33:48.132
I'm your wife. Don't push me away.

01:33:48.220 --> 01:33:50.655
I ain't pushing nobody away.
Just give me some space.

01:33:50.740 --> 01:33:52.971
Just give me some room to breathe.

01:34:23.260 --> 01:34:25.252
All right, Mr. Death.

01:34:30.700 --> 01:34:33.454
I tell you what I'm gonna do.

01:34:33.540 --> 01:34:36.100
I'm gonna take

01:34:36.220 --> 01:34:40.214
and build me a fence
around this yard, see?

01:34:41.700 --> 01:34:45.296
I'm gonna build me a fence
around what belongs to me.

01:34:45.380 --> 01:34:48.452
And then I want you to
stay on the other side.

01:34:48.540 --> 01:34:50.213
You stay over there till
you're ready for me,

01:34:50.300 --> 01:34:51.893
then you come on.

01:34:54.220 --> 01:34:57.816
Bring your army, bring your sickle,
bring your wrestling clothes.

01:34:57.900 --> 01:35:00.051
I ain't gonna fall down
on my vigilance this time.

01:35:00.140 --> 01:35:01.654
You ain't gonna...

01:35:04.740 --> 01:35:06.971
You ain't gonna sneak
up on me no more.

01:35:09.660 --> 01:35:10.889
When you ready for me,

01:35:10.980 --> 01:35:13.336
when the top of your
list say Troy Maxson,

01:35:13.420 --> 01:35:15.491
then you come on up and
knock on the front door.

01:35:15.580 --> 01:35:17.537
Ain't nobody else got
nothing to do with this.

01:35:17.620 --> 01:35:19.498
This between you and me.

01:35:22.100 --> 01:35:23.978
Man to man!

01:35:29.740 --> 01:35:33.575
You stay on the other side of
that fence till you ready for me!

01:35:35.260 --> 01:35:37.775
Then you come up and
knock on that front door

01:35:37.860 --> 01:35:41.490
anytime you want!

01:35:53.620 --> 01:35:55.532
I'll be ready for you.

01:36:39.900 --> 01:36:43.940
<i>Bob Clemente with four home
runs and 24 runs batted in.</i>

01:36:45.300 --> 01:36:46.495
Rose?

01:36:48.780 --> 01:36:51.659
I'm standing here with
my daughter in my arms.

01:36:51.740 --> 01:36:53.732
Now,

01:36:53.820 --> 01:36:56.858
she ain't but a wee,

01:36:58.180 --> 01:36:59.296
bitty little old thing.

01:36:59.380 --> 01:37:01.849
She don't know nothing
about grownfolk business.

01:37:01.940 --> 01:37:03.420
She innocent,

01:37:05.460 --> 01:37:07.656
and she ain't got no mama.

01:37:09.860 --> 01:37:11.772
