01:57:00.460 --> 01:57:03.020
Well, we talk about you.
She heard us talk about you.

01:57:03.620 --> 01:57:06.135
This is your brother, Cory.
Say hello.

01:57:06.220 --> 01:57:07.540
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:57:07.620 --> 01:57:08.849
So, you're Raynell.

01:57:10.140 --> 01:57:12.336
Mama's told me a lot about you.

01:57:12.540 --> 01:57:14.771
Come on, let me fix you some
breakfast. Keep up your strength.

01:57:14.860 --> 01:57:15.930
I ain't hungry, Mama.

01:57:16.140 --> 01:57:18.894
You can fix me something, Rose.
I'll be in there in a minute.

01:57:18.980 --> 01:57:20.380
You sure you don't want nothing,
Cory?

01:57:20.500 --> 01:57:22.059
I know they ain't feeding you right.

01:57:22.140 --> 01:57:23.540
No, Mama, thanks.
I don't feel like eating.

01:57:23.620 --> 01:57:24.690
I'll get something later.

01:57:25.940 --> 01:57:28.614
Raynell, get up there and get
that dress on like I told you.

01:57:39.900 --> 01:57:43.018
I always knew you was gonna
make something out of yourself.

01:57:44.740 --> 01:57:47.255
Your head was always
in the right direction.

01:57:50.260 --> 01:57:51.330
So,

01:57:53.020 --> 01:57:54.739
you gonna stay in?

01:57:54.820 --> 01:57:57.096
Make it a career?
Put in your 20 years?

01:57:57.500 --> 01:58:01.096
I don't know. I got six already.
I think that's enough.

01:58:01.180 --> 01:58:04.776
Stick with Uncle Sam
and retire early.

01:58:04.860 --> 01:58:06.692
Ain't nothing out here.

01:58:08.260 --> 01:58:11.094
I guess Rose told you about
what happened with me.

01:58:13.620 --> 01:58:16.340
They got me down at the workhouse.

01:58:16.420 --> 01:58:19.140
I thought I was being slick
cashing other people's checks.

01:58:20.460 --> 01:58:22.213
How much time you doing?

01:58:23.060 --> 01:58:25.529
They give me three years.

01:58:25.620 --> 01:58:28.772
I got that beat now.
I ain't got but nine more months.

01:58:34.140 --> 01:58:36.530
It ain't so bad.

01:58:36.660 --> 01:58:39.619
You learn to deal with
it like anything else.

01:58:41.900 --> 01:58:43.857
"You got to take the
crookeds with the straights,"

01:58:43.940 --> 01:58:47.138
that's what Papa used to say.

01:58:47.220 --> 01:58:50.816
He used to say that
when he struck out.

01:58:50.900 --> 01:58:53.096
I seen him strike out
three times in a row,

01:58:53.180 --> 01:58:57.413
and the next time up,
he hit the ball over the grandstand.

01:58:57.500 --> 01:59:00.459
Right out there in Homestead Field.

01:59:01.100 --> 01:59:03.032
He wasn't satisfied
hitting in the seats.

01:59:03.102 --> 01:59:04.889
He wanted to hit it over everything.

01:59:06.420 --> 01:59:08.093
Then after the game,

01:59:09.660 --> 01:59:14.177
he had 200 people standing around,
waiting to shake his hand.

01:59:17.580 --> 01:59:20.175
You got to take the
crookeds with the straights.

01:59:23.860 --> 01:59:25.613
Papa was something else.

01:59:26.860 --> 01:59:28.931
You still playing?

01:59:29.020 --> 01:59:30.693
Cory, you know I'm gonna do that.

01:59:31.620 --> 01:59:33.851
We got some fellas down there.
We got us a band.

01:59:33.940 --> 01:59:36.933
We gonna try to stay together
when we get out, but...

01:59:37.020 --> 01:59:38.090
Yeah.

01:59:39.620 --> 01:59:41.691
I'm still playing.

01:59:42.300 --> 01:59:43.814
Still helps me get out
of bed in the morning.

01:59:43.900 --> 01:59:45.095
As long as it do that,

01:59:45.180 --> 01:59:48.617
I'm gonna stick with it,
try to make some sense out of it.

