- Hi.

02:00:29.740 --> 02:00:31.254
You used to sleep in my room?

02:00:32.540 --> 02:00:34.532
Yeah, that used to be my room.

02:00:35.100 --> 02:00:38.013
That's what Papa call it.
"Cory's room."

02:00:40.340 --> 02:00:42.252
Got your football in the closet.

02:00:42.420 --> 02:00:45.413
Raynell. Get up there, get dressed,
and put them good shoes on.

02:00:45.620 --> 02:00:47.851
Mama, can I just wear these?
Them others hurt my feet!

02:00:47.940 --> 02:00:49.818
Well, they're just gonna have
to hurt your feet for a while.

02:00:49.900 --> 02:00:51.052
You ain't said they
hurt your feet when

02:00:51.122 --> 02:00:52.335
you went down to the
store and got 'em.

02:00:52.460 --> 02:00:54.611
They didn't hurt then.
My feet done got bigger.

02:00:54.700 --> 02:00:56.259
Don't give me no back talk!

02:00:56.380 --> 02:00:59.179
Get up there, get dressed,
and put them good shoes on.

02:02:06.860 --> 02:02:09.694
Ain't too much changed.

02:02:09.780 --> 02:02:12.420
He still got that
rag tied to the tree.

02:02:15.700 --> 02:02:17.692
He was out here swinging that bat.

02:02:19.260 --> 02:02:22.094
I was just getting ready
to go back in the house.

02:02:23.380 --> 02:02:26.100
He swung that bat
and just fell over.

02:02:28.620 --> 02:02:30.148
Seem like, when he swung it,

02:02:30.218 --> 02:02:32.455
he stood there with
this grin on his face.

02:02:38.380 --> 02:02:40.053
Then he just fell over.

02:02:42.900 --> 02:02:44.986
They carried him down
there to the hospital,

02:02:45.056 --> 02:02:46.657
but I knew there wasn't no need.

02:02:49.220 --> 02:02:50.841
Why don't you come
on in the house?

02:02:50.911 --> 02:02:52.770
Mama, I got something to tell you.

02:02:54.140 --> 02:02:57.292
I don't know how to tell you this,
but I got to tell you.

02:02:57.420 --> 02:02:59.412
I'm not going to Papa's funeral.

02:03:01.820 --> 02:03:05.575
Boy, hush your mouth.

02:03:05.660 --> 02:03:07.652
That's your daddy you talking about!

02:03:07.900 --> 02:03:09.937
I don't want to hear that
kind of talk this morning.

02:03:10.020 --> 02:03:11.420
I done raised you to come to this?

02:03:11.500 --> 02:03:12.820
You standing there
all healthy and grown,

02:03:12.900 --> 02:03:14.653
talking about you ain't going
to your daddy's funeral?

02:03:14.740 --> 02:03:16.936
- Mama, listen...
- I don't want to hear it, Cory!

02:03:17.020 --> 02:03:18.340
Just get that thought
out of your head.

02:03:18.420 --> 02:03:19.481
I've got to say no to him.

02:03:19.551 --> 02:03:21.060
One time in my life,
I got to say no.

02:03:21.140 --> 02:03:22.654
I don't got to listen to that!

02:03:22.740 --> 02:03:24.333
Now, I know you and your
daddy ain't seen eye to eye,

02:03:24.420 --> 02:03:27.857
but I don't have to listen to
that kind of talk this morning.

02:03:27.940 --> 02:03:30.500
Disrespecting your daddy ain't
gonna make you a man, Cory.

02:03:30.620 --> 02:03:32.339
You gotta find some way to
come to that on your own.

02:03:32.420 --> 02:03:34.889
Not going to your daddy's funeral
ain't gonna make you a man.

02:03:37.940 --> 02:03:40.853
The whole time I was growing up,
living in his house,

02:03:40.940 --> 02:03:43.853
Papa was like a shadow that
followed you everywhere.

02:03:44.620 --> 02:03:47.852
It weighed on you,
and it sunk into your flesh.

02:03:48.540 --> 02:03:50.497
It would wrap around
you and lay there

02:03:50.580 --> 02:03:53.015
until you couldn't tell
which one was you anymore.

02:03:53.140 --> 02:03:57.293
That shadow just diggin'
into your flesh!

02:03:57.380 --> 02:03:59.690
Trying to crawl in.
Trying to live through you.

02:04:00.620 --> 02:04:05.297
Everywhere I looked, I saw Troy
Maxson staring right back at me.

02:04:05.380 --> 02:04:08.532
Hiding under the bed, in the closet.

02:04:08.620 --> 02:04:11.658
I'm just saying I got to find a way
to get rid of that shadow, Mama.

02:04:11.740 --> 02:04:13.971
You just like him.
You got him in you good.

02:04:14.060 --> 02:04:15.210
Don't tell me that, Mama.

02:04:15.300 --> 02:04:18.976
- You Troy Maxson all over again.
- I don't want to be Troy Maxson!

02:04:20.300 --> 02:04:21.893
I just want to be me.

02:04:21.980 --> 02:04:24.893
You can't be nobody but who you are,
Cory.

02:04:24.980 --> 02:04:28.052
That shadow wasn't nothing
but you growing into yourself.

02:04:28.260 --> 02:04:30.217
You either got to grow into it,
or cut it down to fit you,

02:04:30.300 --> 02:04:32.576
but that's all you got
to make a life with.

02:04:32.660 --> 02:04:34.860
That's all you got
to measure yourself

02:04:34.930 --> 02:04:36.654
against the world out there.

02:04:37.660 --> 02:04:40.573
Your daddy wanted you to
be everything he wasn't,

02:04:40.660 --> 02:04:42.174
and at the same time,

02:04:42.260 --> 02:04:45.014
he wanted you to be
everything he was.

02:04:45.340 --> 02:04:47.059
Now, I don't know if
he was right or wrong,

02:04:47.140 --> 02:04:48.256
but I do know

02:04:48.340 --> 02:04:51.333
he meant to do more good
than he meant to do harm.

02:04:53.340 --> 02:04:56.174
Sometimes, when he touched,
he bruised,

02:04:56.940 --> 02:05:00.217
and sometimes,
when he took me in his arms, he cut.

02:05:07.020 --> 02:05:09.171
When I first met your daddy,

02:05:10.100 --> 02:05:11.534
I thought,

02:05:11.780 --> 02:05:14.852
"Here is a man I can lay
down with and make a baby."

02:05:18.460 --> 02:05:21.373
That's the first thing I
thought when I seen him.

02:05:21.460 --> 02:05:23.770
I thought, "Rose Lee,

02:05:24.460 --> 02:05:26.577
"here's a man you can
open yourself up to

02:05:26.660 --> 02:05:28.856
"and be filled to bursting!

02:05:30.380 --> 02:05:35.136
"Here's a man that can fill
up all them empty spaces

02:05:35.220 --> 02:05:37.860
"you been tipping
around the edges of."

02:05:43.140 --> 02:05:46.133
When your daddy walked
through the house,

02:05:46.220 --> 02:05:47.893
he was just

02:05:49.060 --> 02:05:51.416
so big.

02:05:53.140 --> 02:05:54.813
He filled it up!

02:05:57.340 --> 02:06:00.174
That was my first mistake.

02:06:00.260 --> 02:06:02.570
Not to make him leave
some room for me.

02:06:07.180 --> 02:06:09.649
But I wanted a house
I could sing in.

02:06:11.100 --> 02:06:14.332
And that's what your daddy gave me.

02:06:14.420 --> 02:06:16.344
I didn't know to keep
up his strength,

02:06:16.414 --> 02:06:18.494
I had to give up
little pieces of mine.

02:06:20.340 --> 02:06:23.697
I took on his life as mine
and mixed up the pieces,

02:06:23.780 --> 02:06:26.773
so you couldn't hardly
tell which was which.

02:06:29.620 --> 02:06:32.772
It was my choice. My life.

02:06:32.860 --> 02:06:35.853
And I didn't have to
live it like that,

02:06:37.940 --> 02:06:39.335
but that's what life offered me

02:06:39.405 --> 02:06:41.295
in the way of being a woman,
and I took it.

02:06:43.460 --> 02:06:46.294
I grabbed it with both hands.

02:06:46.380 --> 02:06:49.452
And by the time Raynell
came into the house...

02:06:54.460 --> 02:06:58.818
I didn't want to make my blessings
off of nobody's misfortune,

02:07:00.660 --> 02:07:03.732
but I took on to
Raynell like she was

02:07:03.820 --> 02:07:06.972
all them babies I
wanted and never had.

02:07:09.220 --> 02:07:12.213
Like I'd been blessed to
relive a part of my life.

02:07:15.340 --> 02:07:18.492
And if the Lord see fit
to keep up my strength,

02:07:20.580 --> 02:07:24.574
I'm gonna do her exactly
how your daddy did you.

02:07:28.180 --> 02:07:30.934
I'm gonna give her the
best of what's in me.

